00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,074
Watch Movies, Series & LiveTV<br/>www.flixify.app

2
00:00:31,571 --> 00:00:34,490
[FEMALE WHISPERS IN ELVISH]

3
00:00:34,491 --> 00:00:37,743
FEMALE <i>VOICE:<br/>The world is changed.</i>

4
00:00:37,744 --> 00:00:41,497
<i>I feel it in the water.</i>

5
00:00:41,498 --> 00:00:46,001
<i>I feel it in the earth.</i>

6
00:00:46,002 --> 00:00:49,421
<i>I smell it in the air.</i>

7
00:00:49,422 --> 00:00:51,507
<i>Much that once was...</i>

8
00:00:51,508 --> 00:00:53,759
...is <i>lost.</i>

9
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:58,760
<i>For none now live who remember it.</i>

10
00:01:09,734 --> 00:01:14,363
<i>It began with the forging<br/>of the Great Rings.</i>

11
00:01:14,364 --> 00:01:16,448
<i>Three were given to the Elves:</i>

12
00:01:16,449 --> 00:01:21,286
<i>Immortal, wisest and fairest<br/>of all beings.</i>

13
00:01:21,287 --> 00:01:24,122
<i>Seven to the Dwarf-lords:</i>

14
00:01:24,123 --> 00:01:29,002
<i>Great miners and craftsmen<br/>of the mountain halls.</i>

15
00:01:29,003 --> 00:01:30,462
<i>And nine...</i>

16
00:01:30,463 --> 00:01:33,674
<i>...nine rings were gifted<br/>to the race of Men...</i>

17
00:01:33,675 --> 00:01:38,675
<i>...who, above all else, desire power.</i>

18
00:01:39,180 --> 00:01:44,180
<i>For within these rings was bound<br/>the strength and will to govern each race.</i>

19
00:01:45,353 --> 00:01:48,772
<i>But they were all of them deceived.</i>

20
00:01:48,773 --> 00:01:52,234
<i>For another ring was made.</i>

21
00:01:52,235 --> 00:01:55,696
<i>In the land of Mordor,<br/>in the fires of Mount Doom...</i>

22
00:01:55,697 --> 00:02:00,367
...the <i>Dark Lord Sauron forged<br/>in secret</i> a <i>Master Ring...</i>

23
00:02:00,368 --> 00:02:02,619
<i>...to control all others.</i>

24
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:06,790
<i>And into this Ring he poured<br/>his cruelty, his malice...</i>

25
00:02:06,791 --> 00:02:11,791
<i>...and his will to dominate all life.</i>

26
00:02:11,963 --> 00:02:16,675
<i>One Ring to rule them all.</i>

27
00:02:16,676 --> 00:02:18,552
<i>One by one...</i>

28
00:02:18,553 --> 00:02:23,432
<i>...the Free Lands of Middle-earth<br/>fell to the power of the Ring.</i>

29
00:02:23,433 --> 00:02:26,935
<i>But there were some who resisted.</i>

30
00:02:26,936 --> 00:02:31,815
<i>A Last Alliance of Men and Elves<br/>marched against the armies of Mordor.</i>

31
00:02:31,816 --> 00:02:36,816
<i>And on the slopes of Mount Doom, they<br/>fought for the freedom of Middle-earth.</i>

32
00:02:49,250 --> 00:02:54,250
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

33
00:03:06,768 --> 00:03:11,768
<i>Victory was near.</i>

34
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:16,735
<i>But the power of the Ring...</i>

35
00:03:16,736 --> 00:03:21,736
<i>...could not be undone.</i>

36
00:03:42,762 --> 00:03:44,888
<i>It was in this moment...</i>

37
00:03:44,889 --> 00:03:47,474
<i>...when all hope had faded...</i>

38
00:03:47,475 --> 00:03:52,475
<i>...that lsildur, son of the king,<br/>took up his father's sword.</i>

39
00:04:22,677 --> 00:04:27,677
<i>Sauron, the enemy of the Free Peoples<br/>of Middle-earth, was defeated.</i>

40
00:04:36,065 --> 00:04:38,442
<i>The Ring passed to lsildur...</i>

41
00:04:38,443 --> 00:04:43,363
<i>...who had this one chance<br/>to destroy evil forever.</i>

42
00:04:43,364 --> 00:04:45,699
<i>But the hearts of Men...</i>

43
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:48,452
<i>...are easily corrupted.</i>

44
00:04:48,453 --> 00:04:53,453
<i>And the Ring of Power<br/>has a will of its own.</i>

45
00:05:18,274 --> 00:05:22,736
<i>It betrayed lsildur.</i> ..

46
00:05:22,737 --> 00:05:27,737
<i>...to his death.</i>

47
00:05:29,327 --> 00:05:33,413
<i>And some things<br/>that should not have been forgotten...</i>

48
00:05:33,414 --> 00:05:36,583
...were <i>lost.</i>

49
00:05:36,584 --> 00:05:39,002
<i>History became legend...</i>

50
00:05:39,003 --> 00:05:41,213
<i>...legend became myth.</i>

51
00:05:41,214 --> 00:05:44,257
<i>And for<br/>two and a half thousand years...</i>

52
00:05:44,258 --> 00:05:48,595
<i>...the Ring passed<br/>out of all knowledge.</i>

53
00:05:48,596 --> 00:05:52,098
<i>Until, when chance came...</i>

54
00:05:52,099 --> 00:05:56,561
<i>...it ensnared a new bearer.</i>

55
00:05:56,562 --> 00:06:01,562
GOLLUM:<br/>My precious.

56
00:06:01,651 --> 00:06:04,361
FEMALE <i>VOICE: The Ring came<br/>to the creature Gollum...</i>

57
00:06:04,362 --> 00:06:08,573
<i>...who took it deep into the tunnels<br/>of the Misty Mountains.</i>

58
00:06:08,574 --> 00:06:11,701
<i>And there it consumed him.</i>

59
00:06:11,702 --> 00:06:13,954
GOLLUM:<br/>It came to me.

60
00:06:13,955 --> 00:06:18,583
My own. My love. My own.

61
00:06:18,584 --> 00:06:23,584
My precious.

62
00:06:26,926 --> 00:06:30,554
FEMALE VOICE: <i>The Ring brought<br/>to Gollum unnatural long life.</i>

63
00:06:30,555 --> 00:06:34,599
<i>For 500 years it poisoned his mind.</i>

64
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:39,396
<i>And in the gloom of Gollum's cave,<br/>it waited.</i>

65
00:06:39,397 --> 00:06:42,899
<i>Darkness crept back<br/>into the forests of the world.</i>

66
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:45,944
<i>Rumor grew of a shadow in the East...</i>

67
00:06:45,945 --> 00:06:48,947
<i>...whispers of a nameless fear.</i>

68
00:06:48,948 --> 00:06:52,450
<i>And the Ring of Power perceived...</i>

69
00:06:52,451 --> 00:06:57,451
<i>...its time had now come.</i>

70
00:06:57,665 --> 00:07:01,001
<i>It abandoned Gollum.</i>

71
00:07:01,002 --> 00:07:06,002
<i>But something happened then<br/>the Ring did not intend.</i>

72
00:07:06,340 --> 00:07:11,136
<i>It was picked up by the most unlikely<br/>creature imaginable.</i>

73
00:07:11,137 --> 00:07:12,387
BILBO:<br/>What's this?

74
00:07:12,388 --> 00:07:14,014
FEMALE VOICE:<br/><i>A</i> Hobbit.

75
00:07:14,015 --> 00:07:16,975
<i>Bilbo Baggins of the Shire.</i>

76
00:07:16,976 --> 00:07:18,935
A ring.

77
00:07:18,936 --> 00:07:23,565
GOLLUM:<br/>Lost!

78
00:07:23,566 --> 00:07:27,235
My precious is lost!

79
00:07:27,236 --> 00:07:29,779
FEMALE VOICE:<br/>For the <i>time will soon</i> come...

80
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:34,780
<i>...when Hobbits will shape<br/>the fortunes of all.</i>

81
00:07:39,707 --> 00:07:42,959
BILBO:<br/>The 22nd day of September...

82
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:46,379
...in the year 1400...

83
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:49,382
...by Shire-reckoning.

84
00:07:49,383 --> 00:07:54,383
Bag End, Bagshot Row, Hobbiton,<br/>Westfarthing...

85
00:07:55,473 --> 00:07:57,015
...the Shire...

86
00:07:57,016 --> 00:08:02,016
...Middle-earth.

87
00:08:04,482 --> 00:08:09,482
The Third Age of this world.

88
00:08:19,372 --> 00:08:23,917
<i>There and Back Again:</i>

89
00:08:23,918 --> 00:08:25,919
<i>A Hobbit's Tale.</i>

90
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:30,920
By Bilbo Baggins.

91
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:37,138
Now...

92
00:08:37,139 --> 00:08:40,433
...where to begin?

93
00:08:40,434 --> 00:08:45,434
Ah, yes...

94
00:08:45,940 --> 00:08:49,317
"Concerning...

95
00:08:49,318 --> 00:08:51,611
...Hobbits."

96
00:08:51,612 --> 00:08:55,323
<i>Hobbits have been living and farming<br/>in the four Farthings of the Shire...</i>

97
00:08:55,324 --> 00:08:57,492
...for many hundreds of years...

98
00:08:57,493 --> 00:09:00,662
<i>...quite content to ignore<br/>and be ignored...</i>

99
00:09:00,663 --> 00:09:04,165
<i>...by the world of the Big Folk.</i>

100
00:09:04,166 --> 00:09:09,166
<i>Middle-earth being, after all,<br/>full of strange creatures beyond count...</i>

101
00:09:10,006 --> 00:09:13,341
<i>...Hobbits must seem<br/>of little importance...</i>

102
00:09:13,342 --> 00:09:17,554
<i>...being neither renowned<br/>as great warriors...</i>

103
00:09:17,555 --> 00:09:22,555
<i>...nor counted among the very wise.</i>

104
00:09:23,269 --> 00:09:26,146
[KNOCKING]

105
00:09:26,147 --> 00:09:30,358
Frodo! Someone at the door.

106
00:09:30,359 --> 00:09:33,153
<i>In fact, it has been remarked by some...</i>

107
00:09:33,154 --> 00:09:37,949
<i>...that Hobbits' only real passion<br/>is for food.</i>

108
00:09:37,950 --> 00:09:40,326
<i>A rather unfair observation...</i>

109
00:09:40,327 --> 00:09:44,456
...as <i>we have also developed</i> a <i>keen<br/>interest in the brewing of ales...</i>

110
00:09:44,457 --> 00:09:47,625
<i>...and the smoking of pipe-weed.</i>

111
00:09:47,626 --> 00:09:50,628
<i>But where our hearts truly lie...</i>

112
00:09:50,629 --> 00:09:53,465
<i>...is in peace and quiet...</i>

113
00:09:53,466 --> 00:09:55,800
<i>...and good, tilled earth.</i>

114
00:09:55,801 --> 00:10:00,801
<i>For all Hobbits share a love<br/>of things that grow.</i>

115
00:10:04,143 --> 00:10:08,772
<i>And, yes, no doubt to others,<br/>our ways seem quaint.</i>

116
00:10:08,773 --> 00:10:13,773
<i>But today of all days,<br/>it is brought home to me:</i>

117
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:19,570
<i>It is no bad thing<br/>to celebrate a simple life.</i>

118
00:10:22,203 --> 00:10:24,662
[KNOCKING]

119
00:10:24,663 --> 00:10:29,663
Frodo, the door!

120
00:10:31,670 --> 00:10:33,838
Sticklebacks. Where is that boy?

121
00:10:33,839 --> 00:10:38,839
Frodo!

122
00:10:41,347 --> 00:10:46,347
MALE <i>VOICE:<br/>Down from the door where it began</i>

123
00:10:46,519 --> 00:10:49,562
[WAGON RUMBLES]

124
00:10:49,563 --> 00:10:54,359
<i>And I must follow if I can</i>

125
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:58,696
<i>The road goes ever on and on</i>

126
00:10:58,697 --> 00:11:02,367
<i>Down from the door where it began</i>

127
00:11:02,368 --> 00:11:07,368
<i>Now far ahead the road has gone</i>

128
00:11:07,957 --> 00:11:12,957
<i>- And I must follow if I can<br/>- You're late.</i>

129
00:11:15,047 --> 00:11:19,592
A wizard is never late, Frodo Baggins.

130
00:11:19,593 --> 00:11:24,593
Nor is he early. He arrives<br/>precisely when he means to.

131
00:11:35,609 --> 00:11:40,609
It's wonderful to see you, Gandalf!

132
00:11:42,575 --> 00:11:47,575
You didn't think I'd miss<br/>your Uncle Bilbo's birthday?

133
00:11:47,955 --> 00:11:50,623
How is the old rascal?

134
00:11:50,624 --> 00:11:54,377
I hear it's going to be a party<br/>of special magnificence.

135
00:11:54,378 --> 00:11:56,963
You know Bilbo.<br/>He's got the whole place in an uproar.

136
00:11:56,964 --> 00:11:59,132
Well, that should please him.

137
00:11:59,133 --> 00:12:01,259
Half the Shire's been invited.

138
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:06,260
And the rest of them are turning up<br/>anyway.

139
00:12:07,016 --> 00:12:10,518
<i>BILBO:<br/>And so life in the Shire goes on...</i>

140
00:12:10,519 --> 00:12:13,771
<i>...very much as it has<br/>this past Age...</i>

141
00:12:13,772 --> 00:12:18,772
<i>...full of its own comings and goings,<br/>with change coming slowly.</i>

142
00:12:19,486 --> 00:12:22,655
<i>If it comes at all.</i>

143
00:12:22,656 --> 00:12:26,284
<i>For things are made to endure<br/>in the Shire...</i>

144
00:12:26,285 --> 00:12:30,163
<i>...passing from one generation<br/>to the next.</i>

145
00:12:30,164 --> 00:12:35,164
<i>There's always been a Baggins<br/>living here under the Hill...</i>

146
00:12:35,336 --> 00:12:39,464
<i>...in Bag End.</i>

147
00:12:39,465 --> 00:12:42,967
And there always will be.

148
00:12:42,968 --> 00:12:47,805
To tell you the truth,<br/>Bilbo's been a bit odd lately.

149
00:12:47,806 --> 00:12:50,975
I mean, more than usual.

150
00:12:50,976 --> 00:12:54,479
He's taken to locking himself<br/>in his study.

151
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:59,480
<i>He spends hours poring over old maps<br/>when he thinks I'm not looking.</i>

152
00:13:11,330 --> 00:13:16,330
Where's it gone?

153
00:13:39,525 --> 00:13:44,525
He's up to something.

154
00:13:49,994 --> 00:13:52,704
- All right, then. Keep your secrets.<br/>- What?

155
00:13:52,705 --> 00:13:54,580
But I know you have something<br/>to do with it.

156
00:13:54,581 --> 00:13:55,915
Good gracious me.

157
00:13:55,916 --> 00:13:59,043
Before you came along, we Bagginses<br/>were very well thought of.

158
00:13:59,044 --> 00:14:00,378
Indeed.

159
00:14:00,379 --> 00:14:03,131
Never had any adventures<br/>or did anything unexpected.

160
00:14:03,132 --> 00:14:08,132
If you're referring to the incident<br/>with the dragon, I was barely involved.

161
00:14:09,221 --> 00:14:13,016
All I did was give your uncle<br/>a little nudge out of the door.

162
00:14:13,017 --> 00:14:17,520
Whatever you did, you've been officially<br/>labeled a disturber of the peace.

163
00:14:17,521 --> 00:14:22,521
Oh, really?

164
00:14:25,029 --> 00:14:27,697
Gandalf! Gandalf!

165
00:14:27,698 --> 00:14:32,698
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

166
00:14:33,078 --> 00:14:37,415
FEMALE HOBBIT 1:<br/>Fireworks, Gandalf!

167
00:14:37,416 --> 00:14:42,416
FEMALE HOBBIT 2: Gandalf!<br/>MALE HOBBIT: Fireworks, Gandalf!

168
00:14:58,854 --> 00:15:00,438
Gandalf?

169
00:15:00,439 --> 00:15:05,439
- I'm glad you're back.<br/>- So am I, dear boy.

170
00:15:09,031 --> 00:15:14,031
So am I.

171
00:15:28,926 --> 00:15:33,926
Whoa, whoa.

172
00:15:42,648 --> 00:15:44,315
BILBO:<br/>No, thank you!

173
00:15:44,316 --> 00:15:48,486
We don't want any more visitors,<br/>well-wishers or distant relations!

174
00:15:48,487 --> 00:15:53,487
And what about very old friends?

175
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,495
Gandalf?

176
00:15:57,496 --> 00:16:01,165
- Bilbo Baggins.<br/>- My dear Gandalf!

177
00:16:01,166 --> 00:16:06,166
Good to see you. 111 years old!<br/>Who would believe it?

178
00:16:08,090 --> 00:16:13,090
You haven't aged a day.

179
00:16:16,682 --> 00:16:18,850
Come on, come in!

180
00:16:18,851 --> 00:16:22,478
Welcome, welcome.

181
00:16:22,479 --> 00:16:26,691
Oh, here we are.

182
00:16:26,692 --> 00:16:29,318
Tea? Or maybe something<br/>a little stronger?

183
00:16:29,319 --> 00:16:33,322
I've got a few bottles<br/>of the Old Winyard left. 1296.

184
00:16:33,323 --> 00:16:38,323
Very good year. Almost as old as I am.

185
00:16:38,537 --> 00:16:43,207
It was laid down by my father.<br/>What say we open one, eh?

186
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:48,208
Just tea, thank you.

187
00:16:50,215 --> 00:16:52,216
Uh!

188
00:16:52,217 --> 00:16:54,135
I was expecting you sometime<br/>last week.

189
00:16:54,136 --> 00:16:57,638
Not that it matters. You come and go as<br/>you please. Always have and always will.

190
00:16:57,639 --> 00:17:02,639
You caught me a bit unprepared. We've<br/>only got cold chicken and a bit of pickle...

191
00:17:03,061 --> 00:17:06,647
There's some cheese here.<br/>No, that won't do.

192
00:17:06,648 --> 00:17:11,235
We've got raspberry jam,<br/>an apple tart...

193
00:17:11,236 --> 00:17:15,406
But not much for afters.<br/>Oh, no, we're all right.

194
00:17:15,407 --> 00:17:20,407
I've just found some sponge cake.

195
00:17:21,163 --> 00:17:26,163
I could make you some eggs<br/>if you'd--

196
00:17:26,251 --> 00:17:30,087
- Just tea, thank you.<br/>- Oh, right.

197
00:17:30,088 --> 00:17:32,590
- You don't mind if I eat, do you?<br/>- No, not at all.

198
00:17:32,591 --> 00:17:34,133
[KNOCKING]

199
00:17:34,134 --> 00:17:35,593
FEMALE HOBBIT:<br/>Bilbo! Bilbo Baggins!

200
00:17:35,594 --> 00:17:40,594
I'm not at home!

201
00:17:43,185 --> 00:17:45,937
It's the Sackville-Bagginses.

202
00:17:45,938 --> 00:17:48,731
- I know you're in there!<br/>- They're after the house.

203
00:17:48,732 --> 00:17:51,442
They've never forgiven me<br/>for living this long.

204
00:17:51,443 --> 00:17:54,403
I've got to get away from these confounded<br/>relatives, hanging on the bell all day...

205
00:17:54,404 --> 00:17:57,073
...never giving me a moment's peace.

206
00:17:57,074 --> 00:18:00,785
I want to see mountains again.<br/>Mountains, Gandalf!

207
00:18:00,786 --> 00:18:05,456
And then find somewhere quiet<br/>where I can finish my book. Oh, tea.

208
00:18:05,457 --> 00:18:09,627
- So you mean to go through with your plan?<br/>- Yes, yes. It's all in hand.

209
00:18:09,628 --> 00:18:13,965
All the arrangements are made.

210
00:18:13,966 --> 00:18:16,217
Oh, thank you.

211
00:18:16,218 --> 00:18:18,469
Frodo suspects something.

212
00:18:18,470 --> 00:18:21,222
Of course he does. He's a Baggins...

213
00:18:21,223 --> 00:18:24,308
...not some blockheaded Bracegirdle<br/>from Hardbottle.

214
00:18:24,309 --> 00:18:27,979
You will tell him, won't you?

215
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:32,316
- Yes, yes.<br/>- He's very fond of you.

216
00:18:32,317 --> 00:18:36,153
I know.

217
00:18:36,154 --> 00:18:40,157
He'd probably come with me<br/>if I asked him.

218
00:18:40,158 --> 00:18:45,158
I think in his heart, Frodo's<br/>still in love with the Shire.

219
00:18:45,163 --> 00:18:47,665
The woods, the fields.

220
00:18:47,666 --> 00:18:52,666
Little rivers.

221
00:18:54,506 --> 00:18:58,509
I am old, Gandalf.

222
00:18:58,510 --> 00:19:03,510
I know I don't look it, but I'm<br/>beginning to feel it in my heart.

223
00:19:06,018 --> 00:19:08,686
I feel thin.

224
00:19:08,687 --> 00:19:11,689
Sort of stretched...

225
00:19:11,690 --> 00:19:15,192
...like butter scraped<br/>over too much bread.

226
00:19:15,193 --> 00:19:19,864
I need a holiday. A very long holiday.

227
00:19:19,865 --> 00:19:24,865
And I don't expect I shall return.

228
00:19:25,370 --> 00:19:30,370
In fact, I mean not to.

229
00:19:31,209 --> 00:19:36,209
Old Toby. The finest weed<br/>in the Southfarthing.

230
00:19:50,062 --> 00:19:52,688
Ah.

231
00:19:52,689 --> 00:19:55,399
Gandalf, my old friend...

232
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:59,820
...this will be a night to remember.

233
00:19:59,821 --> 00:20:02,990
[CHEERING]

234
00:20:02,991 --> 00:20:07,991
[MUSIC PLAYS]

235
00:20:21,093 --> 00:20:22,426
BILBO:<br/>Hello, hello.

236
00:20:22,427 --> 00:20:27,427
Fatty Bolger. Lovely to see you.<br/>Welcome, welcome.

237
00:20:27,432 --> 00:20:32,432
Go on, Sam. Ask Rosie for a dance.

238
00:20:32,604 --> 00:20:37,274
- I think I'll just have another ale.<br/>- Oh, no, you don't.

239
00:20:37,275 --> 00:20:42,275
Go on!

240
00:20:49,121 --> 00:20:51,247
So there I was...

241
00:20:51,248 --> 00:20:55,459
...at the mercy<br/>of three monstrous trolls.

242
00:20:55,460 --> 00:20:57,628
And they were all arguing<br/>amongst themselves...

243
00:20:57,629 --> 00:21:00,297
...about how they were<br/>going to cook us.

244
00:21:00,298 --> 00:21:05,298
Whether it be turned on a spit, or to sit<br/>on us one by one, squash us into jelly.

245
00:21:06,304 --> 00:21:10,099
They spent so much time arguing<br/>the whithertos and the whyfors...

246
00:21:10,100 --> 00:21:14,645
...that the sun's first light<br/>crept over the top of the trees...

247
00:21:14,646 --> 00:21:18,232
...and turned them all to stone!

248
00:21:18,233 --> 00:21:22,445
RAUGHS]

249
00:21:22,446 --> 00:21:26,282
MERRY:<br/>Quickly.

250
00:21:26,283 --> 00:21:27,992
Whoa!

251
00:21:27,993 --> 00:21:32,955
UP they go!

252
00:21:32,956 --> 00:21:37,956
No, the big one.

253
00:21:43,341 --> 00:21:46,343
Mrs. Bracegirdle, how nice to see you.<br/>Welcome, welcome.

254
00:21:46,344 --> 00:21:48,471
Are all these children yours?

255
00:21:48,472 --> 00:21:53,472
Good gracious,<br/>you have been productive.

256
00:21:53,477 --> 00:21:56,520
FEMALE HOBBIT:<br/>Bilbo?

257
00:21:56,521 --> 00:21:58,439
Sackville-Bagginses!

258
00:21:58,440 --> 00:22:03,440
Quickly, hide!

259
00:22:09,367 --> 00:22:13,037
Thank you, my boy.

260
00:22:13,038 --> 00:22:16,665
You're a good lad, Frodo.

261
00:22:16,666 --> 00:22:19,960
I'm very selfish, you know.

262
00:22:19,961 --> 00:22:23,547
Yes, I am. Very selfish.

263
00:22:23,548 --> 00:22:25,966
I don't know why I took you in<br/>after your mother and father died...

264
00:22:25,967 --> 00:22:28,219
...but it wasn't out of charity.

265
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:29,845
I think it was because...

266
00:22:29,846 --> 00:22:32,473
...of all my numerous relations...

267
00:22:32,474 --> 00:22:36,227
...you were the one Baggins<br/>that showed real spirit.

268
00:22:36,228 --> 00:22:38,229
Bilbo, have you been<br/>at the Gaffer's home brew?

269
00:22:38,230 --> 00:22:40,231
No.

270
00:22:40,232 --> 00:22:43,067
Well, yes, but that's not the point.

271
00:22:43,068 --> 00:22:48,068
The point is, Frodo...

272
00:22:49,407 --> 00:22:54,407
...you'll be all right.

273
00:22:54,746 --> 00:22:57,081
- Done!<br/>- You're supposed to stick it in the ground.

274
00:22:57,082 --> 00:22:58,749
- It is in the ground.<br/>- Outside!

275
00:22:58,750 --> 00:23:03,750
This was your idea.

276
00:23:16,101 --> 00:23:18,769
Bilbo.

277
00:23:18,770 --> 00:23:21,772
Bilbo, watch out for the dragon!

278
00:23:21,773 --> 00:23:26,773
Nonsense. There hasn't been a dragon<br/>in these parts for a thousand years.

279
00:23:38,623 --> 00:23:43,502
- That was good.<br/>- Let's get another one.

280
00:23:43,503 --> 00:23:48,215
GANDALF:<br/>Meriadoc Brandybuck and Peregrin Took.

281
00:23:48,216 --> 00:23:53,216
I might've known.

282
00:23:55,974 --> 00:23:58,934
FEMALE HOBBIT:<br/>Speech, Bilbo!

283
00:23:58,935 --> 00:24:00,477
MALE HOBBIT:<br/>Speech!

284
00:24:00,478 --> 00:24:05,478
Speech!

285
00:24:06,818 --> 00:24:09,904
My dear Bagginses and Boffins...

286
00:24:09,905 --> 00:24:12,281
<i>"Kooks and Brandybucks...</i>

287
00:24:12,282 --> 00:24:14,992
...Grubbs, Chubbs...

288
00:24:14,993 --> 00:24:17,161
...Hornblowers...

289
00:24:17,162 --> 00:24:19,246
...Bolgers...

290
00:24:19,247 --> 00:24:20,998
...Bracegirdles...

291
00:24:20,999 --> 00:24:25,794
-...and Proudfoots.<br/>- Proudfeet!

292
00:24:25,795 --> 00:24:30,758
Today is my 111th birthday!

293
00:24:30,759 --> 00:24:32,509
Happy birthday!

294
00:24:32,510 --> 00:24:36,972
But alas, eleventy-one years is<br/>far too short a time to live among...

295
00:24:36,973 --> 00:24:40,809
...such excellent<br/>and admirable Hobbits.

296
00:24:40,810 --> 00:24:43,687
I don't know half of you<br/>half as well as I should like...

297
00:24:43,688 --> 00:24:48,688
...and I like less than half of you<br/>half as well as you deserve.

298
00:24:51,821 --> 00:24:56,821
I, uh--

299
00:24:58,286 --> 00:25:03,286
I have things to do.

300
00:25:07,045 --> 00:25:12,045
I've put this off far too long.

301
00:25:13,009 --> 00:25:18,009
I regret to announce this is the end!

302
00:25:18,139 --> 00:25:20,391
I'm going now.

303
00:25:20,392 --> 00:25:25,392
I bid you all a very fond farewell.

304
00:25:25,689 --> 00:25:30,689
Goodbye.

305
00:25:32,737 --> 00:25:36,573
[HOBBITS CLAMORING]

306
00:25:36,574 --> 00:25:41,574
[FOOTSTEPS]

307
00:25:50,088 --> 00:25:55,088
RAUGHS]

308
00:26:00,140 --> 00:26:03,434
I suppose you think<br/>that was terribly clever.

309
00:26:03,435 --> 00:26:07,021
Come on, Gandalf.<br/>Did you see their faces?

310
00:26:07,022 --> 00:26:12,022
There are many magic rings in this world,<br/>and none of them should be used lightly.

311
00:26:12,277 --> 00:26:14,653
It was just a bit of fun.

312
00:26:14,654 --> 00:26:19,654
Oh, you're probably right, as usual.

313
00:26:19,743 --> 00:26:23,454
- You will keep an eye on Frodo, won't you?<br/>- Two eyes.

314
00:26:23,455 --> 00:26:26,373
As often as I can spare them.

315
00:26:26,374 --> 00:26:29,752
- I'm leaving everything to him.<br/>- What about this ring of yours?

316
00:26:29,753 --> 00:26:33,714
- Is that staying too?<br/>- Yes, yes.

317
00:26:33,715 --> 00:26:38,677
It's in an envelope over there<br/>on the mantelpiece.

318
00:26:38,678 --> 00:26:43,678
No. Wait, it's...

319
00:26:44,142 --> 00:26:49,142
...here in my pocket.

320
00:26:51,316 --> 00:26:56,316
Isn't that--? Isn't that odd, now?

321
00:26:56,321 --> 00:27:01,321
Yet, after all, why not?

322
00:27:01,409 --> 00:27:06,409
- Why shouldn't I keep it?<br/>- I think you should leave the ring behind.

323
00:27:06,706 --> 00:27:09,083
Is that so hard?

324
00:27:09,084 --> 00:27:12,795
Well, no.

325
00:27:12,796 --> 00:27:16,298
And yes.

326
00:27:16,299 --> 00:27:19,593
Now it comes to it,<br/>I don't feel like parting with it.

327
00:27:19,594 --> 00:27:21,512
It's mine. I found it! It came to me!

328
00:27:21,513 --> 00:27:26,225
- There's no need to get angry.<br/>- Well, if I'm angry, it's your fault!

329
00:27:26,226 --> 00:27:29,269
It's mine.

330
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:32,106
My own.

331
00:27:32,107 --> 00:27:36,276
- My precious.<br/>- Precious?

332
00:27:36,277 --> 00:27:39,363
It's been called that before,<br/>but not by you.

333
00:27:39,364 --> 00:27:42,157
What business is it of yours<br/>what I do with my own things?

334
00:27:42,158 --> 00:27:45,119
I think you've had that ring<br/>quite long enough.

335
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:48,163
- You want it for yourself!<br/>- Bilbo Baggins!

336
00:27:48,164 --> 00:27:52,626
Do not take me for some conjurer<br/>of cheap tricks.

337
00:27:52,627 --> 00:27:57,627
I am not trying to rob you.

338
00:28:01,344 --> 00:28:04,388
I'm trying to help you.

339
00:28:04,389 --> 00:28:09,389
[BILBO WHIMPERS]

340
00:28:11,521 --> 00:28:15,232
All your long years,<br/>we've been friends.

341
00:28:15,233 --> 00:28:19,236
Trust me as you once did.

342
00:28:19,237 --> 00:28:22,197
Let it go.

343
00:28:22,198 --> 00:28:26,743
You're right, Gandalf.

344
00:28:26,744 --> 00:28:30,747
The ring must go to Frodo.

345
00:28:30,748 --> 00:28:33,917
It's late. The road is long.

346
00:28:33,918 --> 00:28:38,918
Yes, it is time.

347
00:28:39,257 --> 00:28:41,758
- Bilbo.<br/>- Hm?

348
00:28:41,759 --> 00:28:46,638
The ring is still in your pocket.

349
00:28:46,639 --> 00:28:51,639
Ah. Yes.

350
00:29:18,963 --> 00:29:23,634
I've thought up an ending for my book:

351
00:29:23,635 --> 00:29:28,635
"And he lived happily ever after<br/>to the end of his days."

352
00:29:28,806 --> 00:29:33,310
And I'm sure you will, my dear friend.

353
00:29:33,311 --> 00:29:37,272
Goodbye, Gandalf.

354
00:29:37,273 --> 00:29:42,273
Goodbye, dear Bilbo.

355
00:29:47,951 --> 00:29:52,951
<i>BILBO:<br/>The road goes ever on and on</i>

356
00:29:54,707 --> 00:29:59,707
Until our next meeting.

357
00:30:24,487 --> 00:30:28,323
<i>BILBO:<br/>It's mine. My own.</i>

358
00:30:28,324 --> 00:30:32,035
<i>My precious.</i>

359
00:30:32,036 --> 00:30:35,163
Riddles in the dark.

360
00:30:35,164 --> 00:30:36,748
Bilbo!

361
00:30:36,749 --> 00:30:41,749
Bilbo!

362
00:30:41,963 --> 00:30:46,508
My precious.

363
00:30:46,509 --> 00:30:48,885
Precious.

364
00:30:48,886 --> 00:30:53,886
He's gone, hasn't he?

365
00:30:54,225 --> 00:30:57,519
He talked for so long about leaving...

366
00:30:57,520 --> 00:31:02,520
...I didn't think he'd really do it.

367
00:31:04,694 --> 00:31:09,694
Gandalf?

368
00:31:14,871 --> 00:31:16,872
Bilbo's ring.

369
00:31:16,873 --> 00:31:19,416
He's gone to stay with the Elves.

370
00:31:19,417 --> 00:31:24,417
He's left you Bag End.

371
00:31:26,132 --> 00:31:28,884
Along with all his possessions.

372
00:31:28,885 --> 00:31:33,885
The ring is yours now.

373
00:31:34,390 --> 00:31:38,060
- Put it somewhere out of sight.<br/>- Where are you going?

374
00:31:38,061 --> 00:31:40,520
- There are some things that I must see to.<br/>- What things?

375
00:31:40,521 --> 00:31:45,521
- Questions. Questions that need answering.<br/>- You've only just arrived.

376
00:31:45,651 --> 00:31:50,651
I don't understand.

377
00:31:51,616 --> 00:31:55,911
Neither do I.

378
00:31:55,912 --> 00:31:58,413
Keep it secret.

379
00:31:58,414 --> 00:32:03,414
Keep it safe.

380
00:32:32,573 --> 00:32:35,158
[GOLLUM SCREAMS]

381
00:32:35,159 --> 00:32:37,661
GOLLUM:<br/>Shire!

382
00:32:37,662 --> 00:32:42,662
<i>Baggins!</i>

383
00:32:53,010 --> 00:32:58,010
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

384
00:33:29,338 --> 00:33:32,424
<i>GANDALF".<br/>"The year 3434 of the Second Age.</i>

385
00:33:32,425 --> 00:33:37,053
<i>Here follows the account of lsildur,<br/>High King of Gondor...</i>

386
00:33:37,054 --> 00:33:42,054
...and <i>the finding<br/>of the Ring of Power. "</i>

387
00:33:44,228 --> 00:33:46,229
<i>"it has come to me.</i>

388
00:33:46,230 --> 00:33:49,900
<i>The One Ring. It shall be<br/>an heirloom of my kingdom.</i>

389
00:33:49,901 --> 00:33:53,570
<i>All those who follow in my bloodline<br/>shall be bound to its fate...</i>

390
00:33:53,571 --> 00:33:57,574
<i>...for I will risk<br/>no hurt to the Ring.</i>

391
00:33:57,575 --> 00:34:00,911
<i>It is precious to me...</i>

392
00:34:00,912 --> 00:34:05,912
<i>...though I buy it with great pain.</i>

393
00:34:06,709 --> 00:34:11,254
<i>The markings upon the band<br/>begin to fade.</i>

394
00:34:11,255 --> 00:34:16,176
<i>The writing, which at first was as clear<br/>as red flame, has all but disappeared.</i>

395
00:34:16,177 --> 00:34:21,177
<i>A secret now<br/>that only fire can tell."</i>

396
00:34:24,769 --> 00:34:29,769
[HOOVES CLOPPING]

397
00:34:36,739 --> 00:34:39,908
Shire.

398
00:34:39,909 --> 00:34:42,410
Baggins.

399
00:34:42,411 --> 00:34:47,411
There's no Bagginses around here.<br/>They're all up in Hobbiton.

400
00:34:48,125 --> 00:34:53,125
That way.

401
00:34:55,633 --> 00:34:58,009
<i>To heal my heart and drown my woe</i>

402
00:34:58,010 --> 00:35:00,512
<i>Rain may fall and wind may blow</i>

403
00:35:00,513 --> 00:35:02,639
<i>But there still be</i>

404
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:04,307
<i>Many miles to go</i>

405
00:35:04,308 --> 00:35:06,434
<i>Sweet is the sound of the pouring rain</i>

406
00:35:06,435 --> 00:35:08,812
<i>And the stream that falls<br/>From hill to plain</i>

407
00:35:08,813 --> 00:35:10,814
<i>Better than rain or rippling brook</i>

408
00:35:10,815 --> 00:35:15,815
<i>ls a mug of beer inside this Took</i>

409
00:35:16,654 --> 00:35:19,948
There's been some strange folk<br/>crossing the Shire.

410
00:35:19,949 --> 00:35:24,286
Dwarves and others of a less<br/>than savory nature.

411
00:35:24,287 --> 00:35:26,329
War is brewing.

412
00:35:26,330 --> 00:35:29,374
The mountains are fair teeming<br/>with goblins.

413
00:35:29,375 --> 00:35:32,168
Far-off tales and children's stories,<br/>that's all that is.

414
00:35:32,169 --> 00:35:36,840
You're beginning to sound like that old<br/>Bilbo Baggins. Cracked, he was.

415
00:35:36,841 --> 00:35:40,010
Young Mr. Frodo here,<br/>he's cracking.

416
00:35:40,011 --> 00:35:41,636
And proud of it.

417
00:35:41,637 --> 00:35:44,055
- Cheers, Gaffer.<br/>- Cheers.

418
00:35:44,056 --> 00:35:48,351
It's none of our concern what goes on<br/>beyond our borders.

419
00:35:48,352 --> 00:35:53,352
Keep your nose out of trouble,<br/>and no trouble'll come to you.

420
00:35:56,027 --> 00:35:58,403
- Good night, lads.<br/>- Good night.

421
00:35:58,404 --> 00:36:03,074
Good night, sweet maiden<br/>of the golden ale.

422
00:36:03,075 --> 00:36:05,660
Mind who you're sweet-talking.

423
00:36:05,661 --> 00:36:10,661
Don't worry, Sam. Rosie knows an idiot<br/>when she sees one.

424
00:36:11,208 --> 00:36:13,043
Does she?

425
00:36:13,044 --> 00:36:18,044
- Good night, Sam.<br/>- Good night, Mr. Frodo.

426
00:36:40,821 --> 00:36:45,821
Is it secret? Is it safe?

427
00:36:45,910 --> 00:36:49,079
[me SQUEALS]

428
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:52,207
Ah.

429
00:36:52,208 --> 00:36:57,208
What are you doing?

430
00:37:06,931 --> 00:37:09,599
Hold out your hand, Frodo.

431
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:14,354
It's quite cool.

432
00:37:14,355 --> 00:37:17,941
What can you see?

433
00:37:17,942 --> 00:37:22,942
Can you see anything?

434
00:37:22,988 --> 00:37:25,073
Nothing.

435
00:37:25,074 --> 00:37:28,118
There's nothing.

436
00:37:28,119 --> 00:37:33,119
Wait.

437
00:37:33,749 --> 00:37:37,460
There are markings.

438
00:37:37,461 --> 00:37:41,089
It's some form of Elvish.<br/>I can't read it.

439
00:37:41,090 --> 00:37:44,175
There are few who can.

440
00:37:44,176 --> 00:37:49,176
The language is that of Mordor,<br/>which I will not utter here.

441
00:37:49,640 --> 00:37:50,974
Mordor!

442
00:37:50,975 --> 00:37:53,184
In the common tongue, it says:

443
00:37:53,185 --> 00:37:56,980
"One Ring to rule them all...

444
00:37:56,981 --> 00:37:59,482
...One Ring to find them...

445
00:37:59,483 --> 00:38:01,985
...One Ring to bring them all...

446
00:38:01,986 --> 00:38:06,614
...and in the darkness bind them."

447
00:38:06,615 --> 00:38:08,825
This is the One Ring...

448
00:38:08,826 --> 00:38:13,826
...forged by the Dark Lord Sauron<br/>in the fires of Mount Doom.

449
00:38:14,331 --> 00:38:19,127
Taken by lsildur<br/>from the hand of Sauron himself.

450
00:38:19,128 --> 00:38:22,130
Bilbo found it.

451
00:38:22,131 --> 00:38:24,299
- In Gollum's cave.<br/>- Yes.

452
00:38:24,300 --> 00:38:29,012
For 6O years, the Ring lay quiet<br/>in Bilbo's keeping...

453
00:38:29,013 --> 00:38:33,057
...prolonging his life,<br/>delaying old age.

454
00:38:33,058 --> 00:38:37,687
But no longer, Frodo.<br/>Evil is stirring in Mordor.

455
00:38:37,688 --> 00:38:40,315
The Ring has awoken.

456
00:38:40,316 --> 00:38:43,234
It's heard its master's call.

457
00:38:43,235 --> 00:38:48,235
But he was destroyed.<br/>Sauron was destroyed.

458
00:38:48,365 --> 00:38:52,869
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

459
00:38:52,870 --> 00:38:55,872
GAN DALF:<br/>No, Frodo.

460
00:38:55,873 --> 00:38:59,375
The spirit of Sauron endured.

461
00:38:59,376 --> 00:39:04,376
His life force is bound to the Ring,<br/>and the Ring survived.

462
00:39:05,049 --> 00:39:08,092
Sauron has returned.

463
00:39:08,093 --> 00:39:10,386
His Orcs have multiplied.

464
00:39:10,387 --> 00:39:14,599
His fortress at Barad-dï¬‚r<br/>is rebuilt in the land of Mordor.

465
00:39:14,600 --> 00:39:19,600
Sauron needs only this Ring to cover<br/>all the lands in a second darkness.

466
00:39:19,605 --> 00:39:21,898
He is seeking it.

467
00:39:21,899 --> 00:39:25,985
Seeking it. All his thought<br/>is bent on it.

468
00:39:25,986 --> 00:39:28,905
For the Ring yearns above all else...

469
00:39:28,906 --> 00:39:32,575
...to return to the hand<br/>of its master.

470
00:39:32,576 --> 00:39:34,494
They are one...

471
00:39:34,495 --> 00:39:37,747
...the Ring and the Dark Lord.

472
00:39:37,748 --> 00:39:39,374
Frodo...

473
00:39:39,375 --> 00:39:41,417
...he must never find it.

474
00:39:41,418 --> 00:39:42,794
FRODO:<br/>All right.

475
00:39:42,795 --> 00:39:47,298
We put it away. We keep it hidden.<br/>We never speak of it again.

476
00:39:47,299 --> 00:39:52,299
No one knows it's here, do they?

477
00:39:55,641 --> 00:39:57,934
Do they, Gandalf?

478
00:39:57,935 --> 00:40:02,605
There is one other who knew<br/>that Bilbo had the Ring.

479
00:40:02,606 --> 00:40:05,775
I looked everywhere<br/>for the creature Gollum.

480
00:40:05,776 --> 00:40:08,152
But the enemy found him first.

481
00:40:08,153 --> 00:40:09,654
[GOLLUM SCREAMS]

482
00:40:09,655 --> 00:40:12,323
<i>GANDALF". I don't know how long<br/>they tortured him.</i>

483
00:40:12,324 --> 00:40:17,036
<i>But amidst the endless screams and<br/>inane babble, they discerned two words:</i>

484
00:40:17,037 --> 00:40:19,330
GOLLUM:<br/>Shire!

485
00:40:19,331 --> 00:40:21,165
Baggins!

486
00:40:21,166 --> 00:40:23,167
Shire.

487
00:40:23,168 --> 00:40:28,168
Baggins. But that would<br/>lead them here!

488
00:40:28,799 --> 00:40:31,676
Who goes there?

489
00:40:31,677 --> 00:40:33,303
Take it, Gandalf!

490
00:40:33,304 --> 00:40:34,554
- Take it!<br/>- No, Frodo.

491
00:40:34,555 --> 00:40:37,140
- You must take it!<br/>- You cannot offer me this ring!

492
00:40:37,141 --> 00:40:41,978
- I'm giving it to you!<br/>- Don't tempt me, Frodo!

493
00:40:41,979 --> 00:40:44,564
I dare not take it.

494
00:40:44,565 --> 00:40:48,151
Not even to keep it safe.

495
00:40:48,152 --> 00:40:50,820
Understand, Frodo...

496
00:40:50,821 --> 00:40:55,821
...I would use this Ring<br/>from a desire to do good.

497
00:40:59,830 --> 00:41:04,830
But through me, it would wield a power<br/>too great and terrible to imagine.

498
00:41:06,170 --> 00:41:10,965
- But it cannot stay in the Shire!<br/>- No.

499
00:41:10,966 --> 00:41:15,966
No, it can't.

500
00:41:17,890 --> 00:41:20,975
What must I do?

501
00:41:20,976 --> 00:41:24,687
- You must leave. And leave quickly.<br/>- Where? Where do I go?

502
00:41:24,688 --> 00:41:28,232
Get out of the Shire.<br/>Make for the village of Bree.

503
00:41:28,233 --> 00:41:29,525
Bree.

504
00:41:29,526 --> 00:41:32,528
- What about you?<br/><i>- I'll</i> be waiting for you...

505
00:41:32,529 --> 00:41:35,198
...at the inn of the Prancing Pony.

506
00:41:35,199 --> 00:41:39,118
- And the Ring will be safe there?<br/>- I don't know, Frodo.

507
00:41:39,119 --> 00:41:42,622
I don't have any answers.

508
00:41:42,623 --> 00:41:47,623
I must see the head of my order. He is<br/>both wise and powerful. Trust me, Frodo.

509
00:41:48,379 --> 00:41:51,130
He'll know what to do.

510
00:41:51,131 --> 00:41:54,217
You'll have to leave the name<br/>of Baggins behind you.

511
00:41:54,218 --> 00:41:57,345
That name is not safe<br/>outside the Shire.

512
00:41:57,346 --> 00:42:01,265
Travel only by day.<br/>And stay off the road.

513
00:42:01,266 --> 00:42:06,266
I can cut across country<br/>easily enough.

514
00:42:06,939 --> 00:42:08,564
My dear Frodo.

515
00:42:08,565 --> 00:42:11,776
Hobbits really are amazing creatures.

516
00:42:11,777 --> 00:42:14,904
You can learn all that there is to<br/>know about their ways in a month.

517
00:42:14,905 --> 00:42:17,448
And yet, after a hundred years...

518
00:42:17,449 --> 00:42:19,742
...they can still surprise you.

519
00:42:19,743 --> 00:42:21,160
[RUSTLING]

520
00:42:21,161 --> 00:42:26,161
Get down.

521
00:42:31,088 --> 00:42:34,757
[GROANING]

522
00:42:34,758 --> 00:42:38,386
Confound it all, Samwise Gamgee!<br/>Have you been eavesdropping?

523
00:42:38,387 --> 00:42:43,057
I haven't been dropping no eaves. Honest.<br/>I was cutting the grass under the window.

524
00:42:43,058 --> 00:42:45,685
A little late for trimming the verge,<br/>don't you think?

525
00:42:45,686 --> 00:42:48,771
- I heard raised voices.<br/>- What did you hear? Speak!

526
00:42:48,772 --> 00:42:50,398
Nothing important.

527
00:42:50,399 --> 00:42:54,694
That is, I heard a good deal about a ring,<br/>a Dark Lord and the end of the world but--

528
00:42:54,695 --> 00:42:59,695
Please, Mr. Gandalf, sir, don't hurt me.<br/>Don't turn me into anything unnatural.

529
00:43:00,117 --> 00:43:02,952
No?

530
00:43:02,953 --> 00:43:05,329
Perhaps not.

531
00:43:05,330 --> 00:43:10,330
I've thought of a better use for you.

532
00:43:10,502 --> 00:43:15,006
GANDALF:<br/>Come along, Samwise. Keep up.

533
00:43:15,007 --> 00:43:17,508
Be careful, both of you.

534
00:43:17,509 --> 00:43:20,511
The enemy has many spies<br/>in his service:

535
00:43:20,512 --> 00:43:25,224
Birds, beasts.

536
00:43:25,225 --> 00:43:28,728
Is it safe?

537
00:43:28,729 --> 00:43:30,313
Never put it on...

538
00:43:30,314 --> 00:43:33,858
...for the agents of the Dark Lord<br/>will be drawn to its power.

539
00:43:33,859 --> 00:43:35,860
Always remember, Frodo...

540
00:43:35,861 --> 00:43:39,447
...the Ring is trying to get back<br/>to its master.

541
00:43:39,448 --> 00:43:44,448
It wants to be found.

542
00:43:48,999 --> 00:43:53,999
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

543
00:44:22,157 --> 00:44:24,700
This is it.

544
00:44:24,701 --> 00:44:27,161
This is what?

545
00:44:27,162 --> 00:44:29,705
If I take one more step...

546
00:44:29,706 --> 00:44:34,706
...it'll be the farthest away<br/>from home I've ever been.

547
00:44:37,881 --> 00:44:42,881
Come on, Sam.

548
00:44:47,808 --> 00:44:50,184
Remember what Bilbo used to say:

549
00:44:50,185 --> 00:44:54,105
-"it's a dangerous business, Frodo."<br/>BILBO: "Going out your door.

550
00:44:54,106 --> 00:44:58,734
<i>You step onto the road,<br/>and if you don't keep your feet...</i>

551
00:44:58,735 --> 00:45:03,735
<i>...there's no knowing where<br/>you might be swept off to."</i>

552
00:45:11,540 --> 00:45:16,540
[suns-me]

553
00:45:16,920 --> 00:45:21,920
Sam.

554
00:45:22,259 --> 00:45:27,259
Wood-elves.

555
00:45:37,107 --> 00:45:41,152
They're going to the harbor<br/>beyond the White Towers.

556
00:45:41,153 --> 00:45:43,529
To the Grey Havens.

557
00:45:43,530 --> 00:45:45,740
SAM:<br/>They're leaving Middle-earth.

558
00:45:45,741 --> 00:45:50,741
FRODO:<br/>Never to return.

559
00:45:50,829 --> 00:45:53,623
I don't know why...

560
00:45:53,624 --> 00:45:58,127
...it makes me sad.

561
00:45:58,128 --> 00:46:03,128
Everywhere I lie there's a dirty<br/>great root sticking into my back.

562
00:46:03,467 --> 00:46:05,343
Just shut your eyes...

563
00:46:05,344 --> 00:46:08,304
...and imagine you're back<br/>in your own bed...

564
00:46:08,305 --> 00:46:13,305
...with a soft mattress<br/>and a lovely feather pillow.

565
00:46:21,568 --> 00:46:24,445
It's not working, Mr. Frodo.

566
00:46:24,446 --> 00:46:29,446
I'm never going to be able<br/>to sleep out here.

567
00:46:29,660 --> 00:46:34,660
Me neither, Sam.

568
00:47:00,524 --> 00:47:03,734
MALE VOICE: <i>Smoke rises<br/>from the Mountain of Doom.</i>

569
00:47:03,735 --> 00:47:05,611
<i>The hour grows late.</i>

570
00:47:05,612 --> 00:47:09,365
<i>And Gandalf the Grey<br/>rides to lsengard...</i>

571
00:47:09,366 --> 00:47:12,034
<i>...seeking my counsel.</i>

572
00:47:12,035 --> 00:47:16,205
For that is why you have come,<br/>is it not?

573
00:47:16,206 --> 00:47:17,748
My old friend.

574
00:47:17,749 --> 00:47:22,749
Saruman.

575
00:47:24,172 --> 00:47:28,009
SARUMAN: You are sure of this?<br/>GANDALF: Beyond any doubt.

576
00:47:28,010 --> 00:47:30,428
So the Ring of Power has been found.

577
00:47:30,429 --> 00:47:33,848
All these long years,<br/>it was in the Shire.

578
00:47:33,849 --> 00:47:37,643
- Under my very nose.<br/>- Yet you did not have the wit to see it.

579
00:47:37,644 --> 00:47:42,644
Your love of the half ling's leaf<br/>has clearly slowed your mind.

580
00:47:43,025 --> 00:47:47,194
But we still have time. Time enough<br/>to counter Sauron if we act quickly.

581
00:47:47,195 --> 00:47:49,572
Time?

582
00:47:49,573 --> 00:47:52,658
What time do you think we have?

583
00:47:52,659 --> 00:47:56,704
Sauron has regained<br/>much of his former strength.

584
00:47:56,705 --> 00:47:59,165
He cannot yet take physical form...

585
00:47:59,166 --> 00:48:02,543
...but his spirit has lost<br/>none of its potency.

586
00:48:02,544 --> 00:48:07,544
Concealed within his fortress,<br/>the Lord of Mordor sees all.

587
00:48:08,175 --> 00:48:13,175
His gaze pierces cloud, shadow,<br/>earth and flesh.

588
00:48:15,599 --> 00:48:19,685
You know of what I speak, Gandalf.

589
00:48:19,686 --> 00:48:24,686
A Great Eye, lidless,<br/>wreathed in flame.

590
00:48:25,901 --> 00:48:27,902
The Eye of Sauron.

591
00:48:27,903 --> 00:48:30,696
He is gathering all evil to him.

592
00:48:30,697 --> 00:48:33,366
Very soon, he'll have summoned<br/>an army great enough...

593
00:48:33,367 --> 00:48:35,910
...for an assault upon Middle-earth.

594
00:48:35,911 --> 00:48:38,788
You know this?

595
00:48:38,789 --> 00:48:40,915
H OW?

596
00:48:40,916 --> 00:48:43,000
I have seen it.

597
00:48:43,001 --> 00:48:46,921
A palantir is a dangerous tool,<br/>Saruman.

598
00:48:46,922 --> 00:48:48,881
Why?

599
00:48:48,882 --> 00:48:53,882
Why should we fear to use it?

600
00:48:54,221 --> 00:48:58,307
They are not all accounted for,<br/>the lost Seeing-stones.

601
00:48:58,308 --> 00:49:03,308
We do not know who else<br/>may be watching.

602
00:49:04,147 --> 00:49:07,066
The hour is later than you think.

603
00:49:07,067 --> 00:49:11,654
Sauron's forces are already moving.

604
00:49:11,655 --> 00:49:14,782
The Nine have left Minas Morgul.

605
00:49:14,783 --> 00:49:15,991
The Nine?

606
00:49:15,992 --> 00:49:19,245
They crossed the River lsen<br/>on Midsummer's Eve...

607
00:49:19,246 --> 00:49:22,123
...disguised as riders in black.

608
00:49:22,124 --> 00:49:27,124
- They've reached the Shire?<br/>- They will find the Ring.

609
00:49:27,671 --> 00:49:30,423
And kill the one who carries it.

610
00:49:30,424 --> 00:49:35,424
Frodo!

611
00:49:44,521 --> 00:49:49,521
You did not seriously think that a Hobbit<br/>could contend with the will of Sauron?

612
00:49:49,693 --> 00:49:54,693
There are none who can.

613
00:49:54,990 --> 00:49:57,867
Against the power of Mordor...

614
00:49:57,868 --> 00:50:02,496
...there can be no victory.

615
00:50:02,497 --> 00:50:06,959
We must join with him, Gandalf.

616
00:50:06,960 --> 00:50:11,960
We must join with Sauron.

617
00:50:11,965 --> 00:50:15,092
It would be wise, my friend.

618
00:50:15,093 --> 00:50:16,719
Tell me...

619
00:50:16,720 --> 00:50:18,804
...friend...

620
00:50:18,805 --> 00:50:23,805
...when did Saruman the Wise<br/>abandon reason for madness?

621
00:51:02,849 --> 00:51:05,684
I gave you the chance...

622
00:51:05,685 --> 00:51:08,521
...of aiding me willingly...

623
00:51:08,522 --> 00:51:13,522
...but you have elected<br/>the way of pain!

624
00:51:35,966 --> 00:51:38,092
SAM:<br/>Mr. Frodo?

625
00:51:38,093 --> 00:51:41,303
Frodo? Frodo!

626
00:51:41,304 --> 00:51:44,723
- I thought I'd lost you.<br/>- What are you talking about?

627
00:51:44,724 --> 00:51:48,561
-It's just something Gandalf said.<br/>- What did he say?

628
00:51:48,562 --> 00:51:52,690
"Don't you lose him, Samwise Gamgee."<br/>And I don't mean to.

629
00:51:52,691 --> 00:51:57,691
Sam, we're still in the Shire.<br/>What could possibly happen?

630
00:51:59,281 --> 00:52:00,573
Frodo.

631
00:52:00,574 --> 00:52:02,992
- Merry, it's Frodo Baggins.<br/>- Hello, Frodo.

632
00:52:02,993 --> 00:52:04,910
Get off him.

633
00:52:04,911 --> 00:52:06,579
Come on, Frodo.

634
00:52:06,580 --> 00:52:08,914
FRODO:<br/>What's the meaning of this?

635
00:52:08,915 --> 00:52:10,916
You've been into Farmer Maggot's crop!

636
00:52:10,917 --> 00:52:13,168
[DOG BARKS]

637
00:52:13,169 --> 00:52:16,297
MAGGOT:<br/>You get back here!

638
00:52:16,298 --> 00:52:17,798
Get out of my field!

639
00:52:17,799 --> 00:52:20,843
You'll know the devil<br/>if I catch up with you!

640
00:52:20,844 --> 00:52:23,971
MERRY: I don't know why he's so upset.<br/>It's only a couple of carrots.

641
00:52:23,972 --> 00:52:25,264
PIPPIN:<br/>And some cabbages.

642
00:52:25,265 --> 00:52:28,350
And those three bags of potatoes<br/>that we lifted last week.

643
00:52:28,351 --> 00:52:32,646
- And then the mushrooms the week before.<br/>MERRY: Yes, Pippin. My point is...

644
00:52:32,647 --> 00:52:35,024
...he's clearly overreacting.

645
00:52:35,025 --> 00:52:40,025
Run!

646
00:52:49,998 --> 00:52:53,626
Oh, that was close.

647
00:52:53,627 --> 00:52:57,755
I think I've broken something.

648
00:52:57,756 --> 00:53:00,299
Trust a Brandybuck and a Took!

649
00:53:00,300 --> 00:53:04,136
What? That was just a detour.<br/>A short out.

650
00:53:04,137 --> 00:53:09,137
- Short out to what?<br/>- Mushrooms!

651
00:53:15,148 --> 00:53:19,401
PIPPIN:<br/>That's mine.

652
00:53:19,402 --> 00:53:21,570
That's nice, Merry.

653
00:53:21,571 --> 00:53:23,781
MERRY:<br/>Here's a nice one, Sam.

654
00:53:23,782 --> 00:53:27,910
I think we should get off the road.

655
00:53:27,911 --> 00:53:32,911
[SCREECHING]

656
00:53:35,502 --> 00:53:37,086
Get off the road!

657
00:53:37,087 --> 00:53:42,087
Quick!

658
00:53:46,930 --> 00:53:51,266
[HOOVES CLOPPING]

659
00:53:51,267 --> 00:53:56,267
Be quiet!

660
00:54:19,879 --> 00:54:24,879
[SNIFFS]

661
00:54:59,085 --> 00:55:04,085
What was that?

662
00:55:20,523 --> 00:55:25,523
[SCREECHES]

663
00:55:33,953 --> 00:55:36,121
SAM:<br/>Anything?

664
00:55:36,122 --> 00:55:38,332
Nothing.

665
00:55:38,333 --> 00:55:41,168
What is going on?

666
00:55:41,169 --> 00:55:46,169
That Black Rider was looking<br/>for something. Or someone.

667
00:55:46,299 --> 00:55:48,509
Frodo?

668
00:55:48,510 --> 00:55:53,510
Get down!

669
00:56:06,486 --> 00:56:09,738
I have to leave the Shire.

670
00:56:09,739 --> 00:56:12,241
Sam and I must get to Bree.

671
00:56:12,242 --> 00:56:15,035
Right.

672
00:56:15,036 --> 00:56:20,036
Bucklebury Ferry. Follow me.

673
00:56:25,588 --> 00:56:28,173
PIPPIN:<br/>Run!

674
00:56:28,174 --> 00:56:33,174
MERRY:<br/>This way! Follow me!

675
00:56:33,721 --> 00:56:38,721
PIPPIN:<br/>Run!

676
00:56:48,027 --> 00:56:52,447
MERRY:<br/>Get the rope, Sam!

677
00:56:52,448 --> 00:56:54,700
Frodo!

678
00:56:54,701 --> 00:56:56,451
PIPPIN:<br/>Run, Frodo!

679
00:56:56,452 --> 00:56:57,744
FRODO: Go!<br/>PIPPIN: Hurry!

680
00:56:57,745 --> 00:57:01,290
MERRY:<br/>Frodo, come on!

681
00:57:01,291 --> 00:57:06,291
SAM: Come on! Faster!<br/>PIPPIN: Jump!

682
00:57:10,258 --> 00:57:15,258
[SCREECHES]

683
00:57:18,266 --> 00:57:23,266
- How far to the nearest crossing?<br/>- The Brandywine Bridge. 2O miles.

684
00:57:37,076 --> 00:57:42,076
Come on.

685
00:57:49,756 --> 00:57:54,756
- What do you want?<br/>- We're heading for the Prancing Pony.

686
00:57:56,679 --> 00:57:59,681
Hobbits. Four Hobbits!

687
00:57:59,682 --> 00:58:04,061
What's more, out of the Shire by your<br/>talk. What business brings you to Bree?

688
00:58:04,062 --> 00:58:08,190
We wish to stay at the inn.<br/>Our business is our own.

689
00:58:08,191 --> 00:58:10,943
All right, young sir.<br/>I meant no offense.

690
00:58:10,944 --> 00:58:13,654
It's my job to ask questions<br/>after nightfall.

691
00:58:13,655 --> 00:58:16,657
There's talk of strange folk abroad.

692
00:58:16,658 --> 00:58:21,658
Can't be too careful.

693
00:58:38,554 --> 00:58:43,554
Out of the way!<br/>Watch where you're walking.

694
00:58:49,399 --> 00:58:54,399
[LAUGHING]

695
00:59:06,207 --> 00:59:08,834
Excuse me.

696
00:59:08,835 --> 00:59:11,837
Good evening, little masters.<br/>What can I do for you?

697
00:59:11,838 --> 00:59:16,838
If you're seeking accommodation, we got<br/>some cozy Hobbit-sized rooms available.

698
00:59:18,136 --> 00:59:23,136
Always proud to cater<br/>to the Little Folk, Mister...?

699
00:59:23,933 --> 00:59:27,269
Underhill. My name's Underhill.

700
00:59:27,270 --> 00:59:29,938
- Underhill, yes.<br/>- We're friends of Gandalf the Grey.

701
00:59:29,939 --> 00:59:33,525
- Can you tell him we've arrived?<br/>- Gandalf?

702
00:59:33,526 --> 00:59:36,111
Gandalf.

703
00:59:36,112 --> 00:59:37,988
Oh, yes...

704
00:59:37,989 --> 00:59:40,449
...I remember. Elderly chap.

705
00:59:40,450 --> 00:59:43,785
Big grey beard, pointy hat.

706
00:59:43,786 --> 00:59:48,786
Not seen him for six months.

707
00:59:52,378 --> 00:59:57,378
What do we do now?

708
01:00:00,887 --> 01:00:02,304
Sam...

709
01:00:02,305 --> 01:00:06,975
...he'll be here. He'll come.

710
01:00:06,976 --> 01:00:11,396
MAN:<br/>Get out of my way!

711
01:00:11,397 --> 01:00:13,315
What's that?

712
01:00:13,316 --> 01:00:15,984
This, my friend, is a pint.

713
01:00:15,985 --> 01:00:17,986
It comes in pints?

714
01:00:17,987 --> 01:00:22,987
- I'm getting one.<br/>- You got a whole half already!

715
01:00:28,039 --> 01:00:33,039
That fellow's done nothing<br/>but stare at you since we arrived.

716
01:00:35,421 --> 01:00:38,715
Excuse me.

717
01:00:38,716 --> 01:00:42,886
That Man in the corner. Who is he?

718
01:00:42,887 --> 01:00:47,557
He's one of them Rangers. They're<br/>dangerous folk, wandering the Wilds.

719
01:00:47,558 --> 01:00:52,558
What his right name is, I've never heard,<br/>but around here he's known as Strider.

720
01:00:54,440 --> 01:00:59,440
Strider.

721
01:01:08,704 --> 01:01:13,704
VOICE OF THE RING:<br/>Baggins.

722
01:01:14,752 --> 01:01:19,752
<i>Baggins.</i>

723
01:01:22,301 --> 01:01:27,301
<i>Baggins. Baggins.</i>

724
01:01:29,267 --> 01:01:32,352
PIPPIN:<br/>Baggins? Sure, I know a Baggins.

725
01:01:32,353 --> 01:01:35,397
He's over there. Frodo Baggins.

726
01:01:35,398 --> 01:01:38,608
He's my second cousin,<br/>once removed on his mother's side...

727
01:01:38,609 --> 01:01:43,609
...and my third cousin, twice removed...

728
01:01:45,408 --> 01:01:50,408
- Pippin!<br/>- Steady on, Frodo.

729
01:02:16,689 --> 01:02:21,689
SAURON:<br/>You cannot hide.

730
01:02:22,111 --> 01:02:26,948
I see you.

731
01:02:26,949 --> 01:02:29,826
There is no life...

732
01:02:29,827 --> 01:02:32,204
...in the void.

733
01:02:32,205 --> 01:02:34,623
Only---...

734
01:02:34,624 --> 01:02:39,624
...death.

735
01:02:42,131 --> 01:02:47,131
You draw far too much attention<br/>to yourself, "Mr. Underhill."

736
01:02:51,682 --> 01:02:52,933
What do you want?

737
01:02:52,934 --> 01:02:55,352
A little more caution from you.<br/>That is no trinket you carry.

738
01:02:55,353 --> 01:02:58,647
- I carry nothing.<br/>Jndeed.

739
01:02:58,648 --> 01:03:01,358
I can avoid being seen if I wish...

740
01:03:01,359 --> 01:03:05,570
...but to disappear entirely,<br/>that is a rare gift.

741
01:03:05,571 --> 01:03:09,449
- Who are you?<br/>- Are you frightened?

742
01:03:09,450 --> 01:03:10,659
Yes.

743
01:03:10,660 --> 01:03:15,660
Not nearly frightened enough.<br/>I know what hunts you.

744
01:03:16,374 --> 01:03:18,583
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

745
01:03:18,584 --> 01:03:22,796
Let him go!<br/>Or I'll have you, Longshanks.

746
01:03:22,797 --> 01:03:27,092
You have a stout heart, little Hobbit.<br/>But that will not save you.

747
01:03:27,093 --> 01:03:30,178
You can no longer wait<br/>for the wizard, Frodo.

748
01:03:30,179 --> 01:03:31,513
They're coming.

749
01:03:31,514 --> 01:03:36,514
[HORSE GRUNTS]

750
01:04:41,334 --> 01:04:46,334
[SCREECHING]

751
01:04:54,889 --> 01:04:58,558
What are they?

752
01:04:58,559 --> 01:05:01,186
They were once Men.

753
01:05:01,187 --> 01:05:03,605
Great kings of Men.

754
01:05:03,606 --> 01:05:07,359
Then Sauron the Deceiver gave to them<br/>nine rings of power.

755
01:05:07,360 --> 01:05:10,695
Blinded by their greed,<br/>they took them without question.

756
01:05:10,696 --> 01:05:14,199
One by one, falling into darkness.

757
01:05:14,200 --> 01:05:19,079
Now they are slaves to his will.

758
01:05:19,080 --> 01:05:20,955
They are the Nazgfil.

759
01:05:20,956 --> 01:05:24,459
Ringwraiths. Neither living nor dead.

760
01:05:24,460 --> 01:05:26,086
At all times they feel...

761
01:05:26,087 --> 01:05:28,213
<i>...the presence of the Ring...</i>

762
01:05:28,214 --> 01:05:33,214
<i>...drawn to the power of the One.<br/>They will never stop hunting you.</i>

763
01:05:42,728 --> 01:05:47,728
FRODO: Where are you taking us?<br/>-lnto the Wild.

764
01:05:53,823 --> 01:05:58,118
How do we know this Strider<br/>is a friend of Gandalf?

765
01:05:58,119 --> 01:06:01,329
I think a servant of the enemy<br/>would look fairer...

766
01:06:01,330 --> 01:06:05,834
-...and feel fouler.<br/>- He's foul enough.

767
01:06:05,835 --> 01:06:08,837
We have no choice but to trust him.

768
01:06:08,838 --> 01:06:13,838
- But where is he leading us?<br/>STRIDER: To Rivendell, Master Gamgee.

769
01:06:14,677 --> 01:06:18,513
- To the house of Elrond.<br/>SAM: Did you hear that? Rivendell.

770
01:06:18,514 --> 01:06:23,514
We're going to see the Elves.

771
01:06:38,576 --> 01:06:42,954
[HOBBITS WHISPERING]

772
01:06:42,955 --> 01:06:47,375
- Gentlemen, we do not stop till nightfall.<br/>- What about breakfast?

773
01:06:47,376 --> 01:06:50,211
- You've already had it.<br/>- We've had one, yes.

774
01:06:50,212 --> 01:06:55,212
What about second breakfast?

775
01:06:55,885 --> 01:06:59,220
Don't think he knows<br/>about second breakfast, Pip.

776
01:06:59,221 --> 01:07:04,221
What about elevenses? Luncheon?<br/>Afternoon tea? Dinner? Supper?

777
01:07:04,685 --> 01:07:09,685
- He knows about them, doesn't he?<br/>- I wouldn't count on it.

778
01:07:14,320 --> 01:07:19,320
MERRY:<br/>Pippin!

779
01:07:32,421 --> 01:07:37,421
What do they eat<br/>when they can't get Hobbit?

780
01:07:56,362 --> 01:08:01,362
[STRIDER HUMS]

781
01:08:03,744 --> 01:08:08,744
[STRIDER SINGS IN ELVISH]

782
01:08:14,588 --> 01:08:17,465
Who is she?

783
01:08:17,466 --> 01:08:22,466
This woman you sing of.

784
01:08:23,472 --> 01:08:26,099
'Tis the lady of LUthien.

785
01:08:26,100 --> 01:08:31,100
The Elf-maiden who gave her love<br/>to Beren, a mortal.

786
01:08:33,107 --> 01:08:37,443
What happened to her?

787
01:08:37,444 --> 01:08:42,444
She died.

788
01:08:43,993 --> 01:08:48,993
Get some sleep, Frodo.

789
01:08:56,589 --> 01:09:00,842
SARUMAN: The power of lsengard<br/>is at your command...

790
01:09:00,843 --> 01:09:05,843
<i>...Sauron, Lord of the Earth.</i>

791
01:09:05,973 --> 01:09:08,641
[VOICES WHISPERING IN BLACK SPEECH]

792
01:09:08,642 --> 01:09:13,642
<i>SAURON".<br/>Build me an army worthy of Mordor.</i>

793
01:09:20,154 --> 01:09:25,033
What orders from Mordor, my lord?<br/>What does the Eye command?

794
01:09:25,034 --> 01:09:30,034
We have work to do.

795
01:10:09,578 --> 01:10:14,578
The trees are strong, my lord.<br/>Their roots go deep.

796
01:10:14,583 --> 01:10:19,583
Rip them all down.

797
01:10:43,862 --> 01:10:48,449
This was the great watchtower<br/>of Amon SUI.

798
01:10:48,450 --> 01:10:53,450
We shall rest here tonight.

799
01:11:02,840 --> 01:11:06,467
These are for you.<br/>Keep them close.

800
01:11:06,468 --> 01:11:11,347
I'm going to have a look around.

801
01:11:11,348 --> 01:11:15,810
Stay here.

802
01:11:15,811 --> 01:11:18,229
MERRY:<br/>My tomato's burst.

803
01:11:18,230 --> 01:11:20,314
PIPPIN:<br/>Could I have some bacon?

804
01:11:20,315 --> 01:11:22,650
MERRY:<br/>Want a tomato, Sam?

805
01:11:22,651 --> 01:11:26,487
- What are you doing?!<br/>- Tomatoes, sausages, nice crispy bacon.

806
01:11:26,488 --> 01:11:29,449
SAM: We saved some for you, Mr. Frodo.<br/>FRODO: Put it out, you fools!

807
01:11:29,450 --> 01:11:33,995
- Put it out!<br/>PIPPIN: That's nice! Ash on my tomatoes!

808
01:11:33,996 --> 01:11:38,996
[RINGWRAITHS SCREECHING]

809
01:11:41,879 --> 01:11:46,879
Go!

810
01:12:37,059 --> 01:12:42,059
Back, you devils!

811
01:12:48,987 --> 01:12:53,987
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>SPEAKS IN BLACK SPEECH]

812
01:13:30,779 --> 01:13:35,779
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>SPEAKS IN BLACK SPEECH]

813
01:14:02,019 --> 01:14:07,019
Frodo!

814
01:14:07,316 --> 01:14:12,316
- Frodo.<br/>- Oh, Sam.

815
01:14:46,188 --> 01:14:49,982
Strider!

816
01:14:49,983 --> 01:14:54,983
- Help him, Strider.<br/>- He's been stabbed by a Morgul blade.

817
01:14:56,990 --> 01:15:01,990
This is beyond my skill to heal.<br/>He needs Elvish medicine.

818
01:15:06,458 --> 01:15:07,708
Hurry!

819
01:15:07,709 --> 01:15:11,879
We're six days from Rivendell!<br/>He'll never make it!

820
01:15:11,880 --> 01:15:14,090
Hold on, Frodo.

821
01:15:14,091 --> 01:15:19,091
Gandalf!

822
01:15:33,235 --> 01:15:38,235
[METAL CLAN KING]

823
01:16:14,067 --> 01:16:19,067
[WHISPERS INSTRUCTIONS TO THE MOTH]

824
01:17:09,706 --> 01:17:14,706
[GROWLS]

825
01:17:54,251 --> 01:17:59,251
Look, Frodo. It's Mr. Bilbo's trolls.

826
01:17:59,506 --> 01:18:04,506
Mr. Frodo? He's going cold.

827
01:18:05,303 --> 01:18:07,263
Is he going to die?

828
01:18:07,264 --> 01:18:12,264
He's passing into the Shadow World.<br/>He'll soon become a Wraith like them.

829
01:18:12,394 --> 01:18:17,314
[RINGWRAITHS SCREECHING]

830
01:18:17,315 --> 01:18:21,318
- They're close.<br/>- Sam, do you know the Athelas plant?

831
01:18:21,319 --> 01:18:22,987
- Athelas?<br/>- Kingsfoil.

832
01:18:22,988 --> 01:18:24,280
Kingsfoil, aye, it's a weed.

833
01:18:24,281 --> 01:18:29,281
It may help to slow the poisoning.<br/>Hurry!

834
01:18:41,798 --> 01:18:46,798
FEMALE: What's this?<br/>A Ranger caught off his guard?

835
01:19:10,827 --> 01:19:13,829
Frodo.

836
01:19:13,830 --> 01:19:18,830
[IN ELVISH]<br/>I am Arwen - I've come to help you.

837
01:19:19,377 --> 01:19:21,462
Hear my voice...

838
01:19:21,463 --> 01:19:26,463
Come back to the light.

839
01:19:28,803 --> 01:19:31,305
Who is she?

840
01:19:31,306 --> 01:19:33,307
[IN ENGLISH]<br/>Frodo.

841
01:19:33,308 --> 01:19:38,308
- She's an Elf.<br/>- He's fading.

842
01:19:39,064 --> 01:19:41,440
He's not going to last.

843
01:19:41,441 --> 01:19:44,860
We must get him to my father.

844
01:19:44,861 --> 01:19:47,905
- I've been looking for you for two days.<br/>- Where are you taking him?

845
01:19:47,906 --> 01:19:52,906
There are five Wraiths behind you.<br/>Where the other four are, I do not know.

846
01:19:55,080 --> 01:19:57,665
[IN ELVISH] Stay with the Hobbits -<br/>I'll send horses for you.

847
01:19:57,666 --> 01:20:00,251
[IN ELVISH]<br/>I'm the faster rider - I'll take him.

848
01:20:00,252 --> 01:20:01,835
The Road is too dangerous.

849
01:20:01,836 --> 01:20:03,295
What are they saying?

850
01:20:03,296 --> 01:20:05,547
ARWEN:<br/>If I can get across the river...

851
01:20:05,548 --> 01:20:09,176
...the power of my people<br/>will protect him.

852
01:20:09,177 --> 01:20:14,177
[IN ENGLISH]<br/>I do not fear them.

853
01:20:14,641 --> 01:20:19,641
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

854
01:20:20,689 --> 01:20:22,273
[IN ENGLISH]<br/>Arvven...

855
01:20:22,274 --> 01:20:27,274
...ride hard. Don't look back.

856
01:20:30,532 --> 01:20:35,532
What are you doing?!<br/>Those Wraiths are still out there!

857
01:21:41,770 --> 01:21:45,064
[SCREECHES]

858
01:21:45,065 --> 01:21:50,065
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

859
01:22:29,526 --> 01:22:33,153
Give up the half ling, She-Elf.

860
01:22:33,154 --> 01:22:38,154
If you want him, come and claim him.

861
01:22:47,794 --> 01:22:52,794
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

862
01:23:29,627 --> 01:23:34,627
No. No!

863
01:23:35,383 --> 01:23:37,885
Frodo, no.

864
01:23:37,886 --> 01:23:40,387
Frodo, don't give in.

865
01:23:40,388 --> 01:23:45,388
Not now.

866
01:23:53,318 --> 01:23:56,487
<i>ARWEN:<br/>What grace is given me...</i>

867
01:23:56,488 --> 01:23:58,572
<i>...let it pass to him.</i>

868
01:23:58,573 --> 01:24:01,325
<i>Let him be spared.</i>

869
01:24:01,326 --> 01:24:05,329
<i>Save him.</i>

870
01:24:05,330 --> 01:24:10,330
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

871
01:24:15,757 --> 01:24:20,757
- Where am I?<br/>GANDALF: You are in the house of Elrond.

872
01:24:21,387 --> 01:24:26,387
And it is 10:00 in the morning<br/>on October 24th, if you want to know.

873
01:24:29,854 --> 01:24:34,854
- Gandalf!<br/>- Yes, I'm here.

874
01:24:35,276 --> 01:24:39,029
And you're lucky to be here too.

875
01:24:39,030 --> 01:24:43,242
A few more hours and you<br/>would have been beyond our aid.

876
01:24:43,243 --> 01:24:48,243
But you have some strength in you,<br/>my dear Hobbit.

877
01:24:54,963 --> 01:24:58,423
What happened, Gandalf?

878
01:24:58,424 --> 01:25:03,424
- Why didn't you meet us?<br/>- I am sorry, Frodo.

879
01:25:08,560 --> 01:25:11,186
I was delayed.

880
01:25:11,187 --> 01:25:16,187
A friendship with Saruman<br/>is not lightly thrown aside.

881
01:25:19,487 --> 01:25:24,449
One ill turn deserves another.<br/>It is over.

882
01:25:24,450 --> 01:25:27,744
Embrace the power of the Ring...

883
01:25:27,745 --> 01:25:32,583
...or embrace your own destruction!

884
01:25:32,584 --> 01:25:36,712
GANDALF:<br/>There is only one Lord of the Ring.

885
01:25:36,713 --> 01:25:41,508
Only one who can bend it to his will.

886
01:25:41,509 --> 01:25:45,721
And he does not share power.

887
01:25:45,722 --> 01:25:50,722
[BIRD SCREECHES]

888
01:25:59,819 --> 01:26:04,819
So you have chosen death.

889
01:26:13,249 --> 01:26:18,003
Gandalf? What is it?

890
01:26:18,004 --> 01:26:20,464
Nothing, Frodo.

891
01:26:20,465 --> 01:26:22,507
SAM:<br/>Frodo!

892
01:26:22,508 --> 01:26:23,759
Frodo!

893
01:26:23,760 --> 01:26:26,345
- Sam.<br/>- Bless you, you're awake!

894
01:26:26,346 --> 01:26:29,306
Sam has hardly left your side.

895
01:26:29,307 --> 01:26:31,850
We were that worried about you.<br/>Weren't we, Mr. Gandalf?

896
01:26:31,851 --> 01:26:36,851
By the skills of Lord Elrond,<br/>you're beginning to mend.

897
01:26:38,483 --> 01:26:43,483
Welcome to Rivendell, Frodo Baggins.

898
01:27:30,118 --> 01:27:33,620
FRODO: Bilbo!<br/>- Hello, Frodo, my lad.

899
01:27:33,621 --> 01:27:38,621
Bilbo.

900
01:27:40,336 --> 01:27:42,337
<i>FRODO".<br/>"There and Back Again:</i>

901
01:27:42,338 --> 01:27:47,338
<i>A</i> Hobbit's Tale, by Bilbo Baggins."

902
01:27:48,136 --> 01:27:52,055
- This is wonderful.<br/>- I meant to go back...

903
01:27:52,056 --> 01:27:56,309
...wonder at the powers of Mirkwood...

904
01:27:56,310 --> 01:27:58,854
...visit Lake-town...

905
01:27:58,855 --> 01:28:02,649
...see the Lonely Mountain again.

906
01:28:02,650 --> 01:28:07,650
But age, it seems,<br/>has finally caught up with me.

907
01:28:19,667 --> 01:28:21,877
FRODO:<br/>I miss the Shire.

908
01:28:21,878 --> 01:28:26,878
I spent all my childhood pretending<br/>I was off somewhere else.

909
01:28:27,341 --> 01:28:32,341
Off with you,<br/>on one of your adventures.

910
01:28:33,890 --> 01:28:38,890
But my own adventure turned out<br/>to be quite different.

911
01:28:42,690 --> 01:28:47,027
I'm not like you, Bilbo.

912
01:28:47,028 --> 01:28:52,028
My dear boy.

913
01:28:53,451 --> 01:28:58,205
SAM: Now, what have I forgotten?<br/>- Packed already?

914
01:28:58,206 --> 01:29:00,207
No harm in being prepared.

915
01:29:00,208 --> 01:29:02,959
- I thought you wanted to see the Elves.<br/>- I do.

916
01:29:02,960 --> 01:29:06,046
- More than anything.<br/>- I did.

917
01:29:06,047 --> 01:29:08,715
It's just...

918
01:29:08,716 --> 01:29:11,551
We did what Gandalf wanted, didn't we?

919
01:29:11,552 --> 01:29:15,430
We got the Ring this far,<br/>to Rivendell. And I thought...

920
01:29:15,431 --> 01:29:18,934
...seeing as how you're on the mend,<br/>we'd be off soon.

921
01:29:18,935 --> 01:29:23,935
Off home.

922
01:29:24,816 --> 01:29:28,985
You are right, Sam.

923
01:29:28,986 --> 01:29:32,322
We did what we set out to do.

924
01:29:32,323 --> 01:29:37,323
The Ring will be safe in Rivendell.

925
01:29:38,996 --> 01:29:42,082
I am ready to go home.

926
01:29:42,083 --> 01:29:44,334
ELROND:<br/>His strength returns.

927
01:29:44,335 --> 01:29:49,335
That wound will never fully heal.<br/>He will carry it the rest of his life.

928
01:29:50,591 --> 01:29:53,343
And yet to have come so far<br/>still bearing the Ring...

929
01:29:53,344 --> 01:29:57,264
...the Hobbit has shown extraordinary<br/>resilience to its evil.

930
01:29:57,265 --> 01:30:00,851
It is a burden he should never<br/>have had to bear.

931
01:30:00,852 --> 01:30:05,852
- We can ask no more of Frodo.<br/>- Gandalf, the enemy is moving.

932
01:30:06,482 --> 01:30:11,361
Sauron's forces are massing in the East.<br/>His Eye is fixed on Rivendell.

933
01:30:11,362 --> 01:30:14,281
And Saruman, you tell me, has betrayed us.

934
01:30:14,282 --> 01:30:18,285
Our list of allies grows thin.

935
01:30:18,286 --> 01:30:21,288
His treachery runs deeper<br/>than you know.

936
01:30:21,289 --> 01:30:25,125
By foul craft, Saruman<br/>has crossed Orcs with Goblin-men.

937
01:30:25,126 --> 01:30:27,878
He's breeding an army<br/>in the caverns of lsengard.

938
01:30:27,879 --> 01:30:32,632
An army that can move in sunlight<br/>and cover great distance at speed.

939
01:30:32,633 --> 01:30:35,510
Saruman is coming for the Ring.

940
01:30:35,511 --> 01:30:39,764
This evil cannot be concealed<br/>by the power of the Elves.

941
01:30:39,765 --> 01:30:44,765
We do not have the strength<br/>to fight both Mordor and lsengard!

942
01:30:47,982 --> 01:30:50,400
Gandalf...

943
01:30:50,401 --> 01:30:55,401
...the Ring cannot stay here.

944
01:31:12,506 --> 01:31:15,926
ELROND: <i>This peril belongs<br/>to all Middle-earth.</i>

945
01:31:15,927 --> 01:31:19,679
<i>They must decide now how to end it.</i>

946
01:31:19,680 --> 01:31:23,934
The time of the Elves is over.<br/>My people are leaving these shores.

947
01:31:23,935 --> 01:31:27,687
Who will you look to when we've gone?<br/>The Dwarves?

948
01:31:27,688 --> 01:31:32,688
They hide in mountains seeking riches.<br/>They care not for the troubles of others.

949
01:31:34,445 --> 01:31:37,614
It is in Men<br/>that we must place our hope.

950
01:31:37,615 --> 01:31:40,200
Men?

951
01:31:40,201 --> 01:31:43,620
Men are weak.<br/>The race of Men is failing.

952
01:31:43,621 --> 01:31:48,375
The blood of NUmenor is all but spent,<br/>its pride and dignity forgotten.

953
01:31:48,376 --> 01:31:52,087
It is because of Men<br/>the Ring survives.

954
01:31:52,088 --> 01:31:54,381
I was there, Gandalf.

955
01:31:54,382 --> 01:31:59,382
<i>I was there 3000 years ago...</i>

956
01:32:04,058 --> 01:32:06,643
<i>...when lsildur took the Ring.</i>

957
01:32:06,644 --> 01:32:11,644
I was there the day<br/>the strength of Men failed.

958
01:32:13,109 --> 01:32:17,237
lsildur, hurry! Follow me.

959
01:32:17,238 --> 01:32:21,116
<i>ELROND". I led lsildur into the heart<br/>of Mount Doom...</i>

960
01:32:21,117 --> 01:32:24,828
<i>...where the Ring was forged,<br/>the one place it could be destroyed.</i>

961
01:32:24,829 --> 01:32:27,747
Cast it into the fire!

962
01:32:27,748 --> 01:32:32,585
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

963
01:32:32,586 --> 01:32:37,586
- Destroy it!<br/>- No.

964
01:32:37,717 --> 01:32:40,343
lsildur!

965
01:32:40,344 --> 01:32:45,344
ELROND: <i>It should have ended that day,<br/>but evil was allowed to endure.</i>

966
01:32:49,186 --> 01:32:54,186
lsildur kept the Ring.<br/>The line of kings is broken.

967
01:32:54,358 --> 01:32:58,194
There's no strength left<br/>in the world of Men.

968
01:32:58,195 --> 01:33:03,195
- They're scattered, divided, leaderless.<br/>- There is one who could unite them.

969
01:33:03,242 --> 01:33:08,242
One who could reclaim<br/>the throne of Gondor.

970
01:33:08,289 --> 01:33:12,292
He turned from that path<br/>a long time ago.

971
01:33:12,293 --> 01:33:17,293
He has chosen exile.

972
01:33:45,659 --> 01:33:47,827
You are no Elf.

973
01:33:47,828 --> 01:33:50,497
Men of the South are welcome here.

974
01:33:50,498 --> 01:33:55,498
- Who are you?<br/>- I am a friend to Gandalf the Grey.

975
01:33:55,503 --> 01:33:58,713
Then we are here on common purpose...

976
01:33:58,714 --> 01:34:03,714
...friend.

977
01:34:15,356 --> 01:34:20,356
The shards of Narsil.

978
01:34:21,737 --> 01:34:26,737
The blade that cut the Ring<br/>from Sauron's hand.

979
01:34:29,120 --> 01:34:34,120
It's still sharp.

980
01:34:40,256 --> 01:34:45,256
But no more than a broken heirloom.

981
01:35:10,161 --> 01:35:14,080
Why do you fear the past?

982
01:35:14,081 --> 01:35:19,081
You are lsildur's heir,<br/>not lsildur himself.

983
01:35:19,670 --> 01:35:23,590
You are not bound to his fate.

984
01:35:23,591 --> 01:35:28,591
The same blood ï¬‚ows in my veins.

985
01:35:30,598 --> 01:35:35,598
The same weakness.

986
01:35:35,895 --> 01:35:38,897
Your time will come.

987
01:35:38,898 --> 01:35:43,898
You will face the same evil.<br/>And you will defeat it.

988
01:35:46,447 --> 01:35:49,824
[IN ELVISH]<br/>The Shadow does not hold sway yet.

989
01:35:49,825 --> 01:35:54,825
Not over you... not over me.

990
01:36:04,798 --> 01:36:09,798
Do you remember when we first met?

991
01:36:11,555 --> 01:36:16,555
[IN ELVISH]<br/>[thought I had strayed into a dream.

992
01:36:16,644 --> 01:36:20,855
Long years have passed.

993
01:36:20,856 --> 01:36:25,693
You did not have the cares you carry now.

994
01:36:25,694 --> 01:36:30,694
Do you remember what I told you?

995
01:36:33,827 --> 01:36:38,498
[IN ENGLISH]<br/>You said you'd bind yourself to me...

996
01:36:38,499 --> 01:36:43,499
...forsaking the immortal life<br/>of your people.

997
01:36:44,630 --> 01:36:46,673
[IN ENGLISH]<br/>And to that I hold.

998
01:36:46,674 --> 01:36:50,551
I would rather share<br/>one lifetime with you...

999
01:36:50,552 --> 01:36:55,552
...than face all the Ages<br/>of this world alone.

1000
01:37:03,190 --> 01:37:07,986
I choose a mortal life.

1001
01:37:07,987 --> 01:37:12,987
- You cannot give me this.<br/>- It is mine to give to whom I will...

1002
01:37:15,494 --> 01:37:20,494
...like my heart.

1003
01:37:33,762 --> 01:37:37,682
ELROND: Strangers from distant lands,<br/>friends of old...

1004
01:37:37,683 --> 01:37:42,228
...you've been summoned here<br/>to answer the threat of Mordor.

1005
01:37:42,229 --> 01:37:47,229
Middle-earth stands upon the brink<br/>of destruction. None can escape it.

1006
01:37:47,359 --> 01:37:51,070
You will unite, or you will fall.

1007
01:37:51,071 --> 01:37:56,071
Each race is bound to this fate,<br/>this one doom.

1008
01:37:57,202 --> 01:38:02,202
Bring forth the Ring, Frodo.

1009
01:38:14,762 --> 01:38:19,762
So it is true.

1010
01:38:33,947 --> 01:38:37,658
In a dream...

1011
01:38:37,659 --> 01:38:41,079
...I saw the eastern sky grow dark...

1012
01:38:41,080 --> 01:38:43,581
...but in the West<br/>a pale light lingered.

1013
01:38:43,582 --> 01:38:45,625
A voice was crying:

1014
01:38:45,626 --> 01:38:49,545
"Your doom is near at hand.

1015
01:38:49,546 --> 01:38:54,546
lsildur's Bane is found."

1016
01:38:56,303 --> 01:38:58,805
lsildur's Bane.

1017
01:38:58,806 --> 01:39:00,306
Boromir!

1018
01:39:00,307 --> 01:39:04,435
[GANDALF CHANTS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1019
01:39:04,436 --> 01:39:09,436
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>ECHOES IN BLACK SPEECH]

1020
01:39:23,288 --> 01:39:27,291
Never before has any voice uttered the<br/>words of that tongue here in lmladris.

1021
01:39:27,292 --> 01:39:31,170
I do not ask your pardon,<br/>Master Elrond...

1022
01:39:31,171 --> 01:39:33,589
...for the Black Speech of Mordor...

1023
01:39:33,590 --> 01:39:35,133
...may yet be heard...

1024
01:39:35,134 --> 01:39:38,302
...in every corner of the West!

1025
01:39:38,303 --> 01:39:41,305
The Ring is altogether evil.

1026
01:39:41,306 --> 01:39:43,391
It is a gift.

1027
01:39:43,392 --> 01:39:46,102
A gift to the foes of Mordor.

1028
01:39:46,103 --> 01:39:48,396
Why not use this Ring?

1029
01:39:48,397 --> 01:39:51,357
Long has my father,<br/>the Steward of Gondor...

1030
01:39:51,358 --> 01:39:55,987
...kept the forces of Mordor at bay.<br/>By the blood of our people...

1031
01:39:55,988 --> 01:39:59,991
...are your lands kept safe.

1032
01:39:59,992 --> 01:40:04,620
Give Gondor the weapon of the enemy.<br/>Let us use it against him.

1033
01:40:04,621 --> 01:40:09,000
You cannot wield it.<br/>None of us can.

1034
01:40:09,001 --> 01:40:13,212
The One Ring answers to Sauron alone.<br/>It has no other master.

1035
01:40:13,213 --> 01:40:17,049
And what would a Ranger know<br/>of this matter?

1036
01:40:17,050 --> 01:40:20,052
This is no mere Ranger.

1037
01:40:20,053 --> 01:40:24,223
He is Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

1038
01:40:24,224 --> 01:40:29,224
You owe him your allegiance.

1039
01:40:31,231 --> 01:40:34,901
Aragorn.

1040
01:40:34,902 --> 01:40:39,902
This is lsildur's heir?

1041
01:40:40,073 --> 01:40:44,911
And heir to the throne of Gondor.

1042
01:40:44,912 --> 01:40:49,749
[IN ELVISH]<br/>Sit down, Legolas.

1043
01:40:49,750 --> 01:40:54,420
Gondor has no king.

1044
01:40:54,421 --> 01:40:59,421
Gondor needs no king.

1045
01:41:02,763 --> 01:41:07,433
Aragorn is right. We cannot use it.

1046
01:41:07,434 --> 01:41:11,187
You have only one choice.

1047
01:41:11,188 --> 01:41:15,399
The Ring must be destroyed.

1048
01:41:15,400 --> 01:41:18,778
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1049
01:41:18,779 --> 01:41:23,779
What are we waiting for?

1050
01:41:27,246 --> 01:41:32,246
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>SPEAKS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1051
01:41:33,460 --> 01:41:36,712
The Ring cannot be destroyed, Gimli,<br/>son of GlÃ©in...

1052
01:41:36,713 --> 01:41:41,467
...by any craft that we here possess.

1053
01:41:41,468 --> 01:41:45,805
The Ring was made in the fires<br/>of Mount Doom.

1054
01:41:45,806 --> 01:41:50,685
Only there can it be unmade.

1055
01:41:50,686 --> 01:41:53,479
It must be taken deep into Mordor...

1056
01:41:53,480 --> 01:41:58,480
...and cast back into the fiery chasm<br/>from whence it came.

1057
01:41:58,652 --> 01:42:00,486
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1058
01:42:00,487 --> 01:42:02,989
One of you...

1059
01:42:02,990 --> 01:42:07,990
...must do this.

1060
01:42:08,078 --> 01:42:12,665
One does not simply walk into Mordor.

1061
01:42:12,666 --> 01:42:17,169
Its Black Gates are guarded<br/>by more than just Orcs.

1062
01:42:17,170 --> 01:42:21,507
There is evil there<br/>that does not sleep.

1063
01:42:21,508 --> 01:42:26,508
The Great Eye is ever-watchful.

1064
01:42:26,513 --> 01:42:28,723
It is a barren wasteland...

1065
01:42:28,724 --> 01:42:32,518
...riddled with fire, and ash<br/>and dust.

1066
01:42:32,519 --> 01:42:36,606
The very air you breathe<br/>is a poisonous fume.

1067
01:42:36,607 --> 01:42:41,110
Not with 10,000 men<br/>could you do this. It is folly.

1068
01:42:41,111 --> 01:42:45,740
Have you heard nothing Lord Elrond<br/>has said? The Ring must be destroyed.

1069
01:42:45,741 --> 01:42:48,534
And I suppose you think<br/>you are the one to do it!

1070
01:42:48,535 --> 01:42:53,372
And if we fail, what then? What happens<br/>when Sauron takes back what is his?

1071
01:42:53,373 --> 01:42:58,373
I will be dead before I see the Ring<br/>in the hands of an Elf!

1072
01:42:58,879 --> 01:43:00,713
[SHOUTING]

1073
01:43:00,714 --> 01:43:04,383
Never trust an Elf!

1074
01:43:04,384 --> 01:43:09,384
GANDALF: Do you not understand?<br/>While you bicker, Sauron's power grows!

1075
01:43:10,557 --> 01:43:14,727
None can escape it!<br/>You'll all be destroyed!

1076
01:43:14,728 --> 01:43:19,728
[VOICE OF THE RING<br/>WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1077
01:43:32,204 --> 01:43:36,415
I will take it.

1078
01:43:36,416 --> 01:43:41,416
I will take it.

1079
01:43:44,758 --> 01:43:49,758
I will take the Ring to Mordor.

1080
01:43:55,852 --> 01:44:00,189
Though...

1081
01:44:00,190 --> 01:44:04,026
...I do not know the way.

1082
01:44:04,027 --> 01:44:08,531
I will help you bear<br/>this burden, Frodo Baggins...

1083
01:44:08,532 --> 01:44:13,035
...as long as it is yours to bear.

1084
01:44:13,036 --> 01:44:16,872
If by my life<br/>or death I can protect you...

1085
01:44:16,873 --> 01:44:21,419
...I Will.

1086
01:44:21,420 --> 01:44:25,548
You have my sword.

1087
01:44:25,549 --> 01:44:28,217
And you have my bow.

1088
01:44:28,218 --> 01:44:33,218
And my ax.

1089
01:44:37,728 --> 01:44:42,728
You carry the fates<br/>of us all, little one.

1090
01:44:42,733 --> 01:44:46,861
If this is indeed<br/>the will of the Council...

1091
01:44:46,862 --> 01:44:51,862
-...then Gondor will see it done.<br/>- Hey!

1092
01:44:51,908 --> 01:44:56,871
- Frodo's not going anywhere without me.<br/>- It is hardly possible to separate you...

1093
01:44:56,872 --> 01:45:01,872
...even when he is summoned<br/>to a secret Council and you are not.

1094
01:45:02,252 --> 01:45:06,338
We're coming too!

1095
01:45:06,339 --> 01:45:09,341
You'll have to send us home<br/>tied up in a sack to stop us.

1096
01:45:09,342 --> 01:45:13,012
Anyway, you need people<br/>of intelligence on this sort of...

1097
01:45:13,013 --> 01:45:14,513
...mission.

1098
01:45:14,514 --> 01:45:16,474
Quest.

1099
01:45:16,475 --> 01:45:19,351
Thing.

1100
01:45:19,352 --> 01:45:23,606
Well, that rules you out, Pip.

1101
01:45:23,607 --> 01:45:27,359
Nine companions.

1102
01:45:27,360 --> 01:45:29,528
So be it.

1103
01:45:29,529 --> 01:45:33,199
You shall be<br/>the Fellowship of the Ring.

1104
01:45:33,200 --> 01:45:35,242
Great!

1105
01:45:35,243 --> 01:45:40,243
Where are we going?

1106
01:46:13,865 --> 01:46:18,244
ELROND [IN ELVISH]:<br/>She wanted to protect her child...

1107
01:46:18,245 --> 01:46:23,245
she thought in Rivendell<br/>you would be safe.

1108
01:46:24,376 --> 01:46:28,379
[IN ENGLISH] In her heart, your mother<br/>knew you'd be hunted all your life.

1109
01:46:28,380 --> 01:46:30,547
That you'd never escape your fate.

1110
01:46:30,548 --> 01:46:34,635
The skill of the Elves<br/>can reforge the sword of kings...

1111
01:46:34,636 --> 01:46:39,556
...but only you have the power<br/>to wield it.

1112
01:46:39,557 --> 01:46:42,226
I do not want that power.

1113
01:46:42,227 --> 01:46:46,230
I have never wanted it.

1114
01:46:46,231 --> 01:46:51,231
You are the last of that bloodline.<br/>There is no other.

1115
01:46:53,238 --> 01:46:55,781
BILBO:<br/>My old sword! Sting.

1116
01:46:55,782 --> 01:47:00,782
Here, take it. Take it.

1117
01:47:02,414 --> 01:47:07,084
-It's so light.<br/>- Yes. Made by the Elves, you know.

1118
01:47:07,085 --> 01:47:11,380
The blade glows blue<br/>when Orcs are close.

1119
01:47:11,381 --> 01:47:16,135
And it's times like that, my lad,<br/>when you have to be extra careful.

1120
01:47:16,136 --> 01:47:19,013
Here's a pretty thing.

1121
01:47:19,014 --> 01:47:21,098
Mithril.

1122
01:47:21,099 --> 01:47:25,686
As light as a feather,<br/>and as hard as dragon scales.

1123
01:47:25,687 --> 01:47:30,687
Let me see you put it on. Come on.

1124
01:47:32,485 --> 01:47:36,989
Uh!

1125
01:47:36,990 --> 01:47:40,284
My old ring.

1126
01:47:40,285 --> 01:47:44,455
I should very much like...

1127
01:47:44,456 --> 01:47:49,456
...to hold it again, one last time.

1128
01:48:05,810 --> 01:48:09,813
I'm sorry I brought this upon you,<br/>my boy.

1129
01:48:09,814 --> 01:48:14,814
I'm sorry that you<br/>must carry this burden.

1130
01:48:18,448 --> 01:48:23,448
I'm sorry for everything.

1131
01:48:36,549 --> 01:48:41,549
The Ring-bearer is setting out<br/>on the Quest of Mount Doom.

1132
01:48:42,055 --> 01:48:44,890
On you who travel with him,<br/>no oath...

1133
01:48:44,891 --> 01:48:49,891
...nor bond is laid to go further<br/>than you will.

1134
01:48:51,481 --> 01:48:54,483
Farewell. Hold to your purpose.

1135
01:48:54,484 --> 01:48:58,946
May the blessings of Elves and Men...

1136
01:48:58,947 --> 01:49:03,947
...and all Free Folk go with you.

1137
01:49:04,619 --> 01:49:09,619
The Fellowship awaits the Ring-bearer.

1138
01:49:27,142 --> 01:49:30,185
Mordor, Gandalf, is it left or right?

1139
01:49:30,186 --> 01:49:35,186
Left.

1140
01:50:51,518 --> 01:50:56,146
<i>GAN DALF: We must hold to this course,<br/>west of the Misty Mountains, for 40 days.</i>

1141
01:50:56,147 --> 01:51:00,108
<i>If our luck holds, the Gap of Rohan<br/>will still be open to us.</i>

1142
01:51:00,109 --> 01:51:03,820
<i>From there, our road<br/>turns east to Mordor.</i>

1143
01:51:03,821 --> 01:51:08,821
Two, one, five. Good! Very good.

1144
01:51:09,494 --> 01:51:10,744
Move your feet.

1145
01:51:10,745 --> 01:51:12,287
MERRY: You look good, Pippin.<br/>- Thanks.

1146
01:51:12,288 --> 01:51:15,040
BOROMIR:<br/>Faster!

1147
01:51:15,041 --> 01:51:19,044
If anyone was to ask for my opinion,<br/>which I note they're not...

1148
01:51:19,045 --> 01:51:22,297
...I'd say we were taking<br/>the long way 'round.

1149
01:51:22,298 --> 01:51:26,009
Gandalf, we could pass through<br/>the Mines of Moria.

1150
01:51:26,010 --> 01:51:30,180
My cousin Balin would give us<br/>a royal welcome.

1151
01:51:30,181 --> 01:51:35,181
No, I would not take the road through<br/>Moria unless I had no other choice.

1152
01:51:44,779 --> 01:51:46,697
Sorry!

1153
01:51:46,698 --> 01:51:49,533
MERRY:<br/>Get him!

1154
01:51:49,534 --> 01:51:52,536
MERRY: For the Shire!<br/>PIPPIN: Hold him. Hold him down, Merry!

1155
01:51:52,537 --> 01:51:57,537
Gentlemen, that's enough.

1156
01:51:58,668 --> 01:52:00,711
MERRY: You've got my arm!<br/>You've got my arm!

1157
01:52:00,712 --> 01:52:03,630
- What is that?<br/>- Nothing. It's just a wisp of cloud.

1158
01:52:03,631 --> 01:52:06,550
It's moving fast.

1159
01:52:06,551 --> 01:52:09,511
Against the wind.

1160
01:52:09,512 --> 01:52:11,847
- Crebain from Dunland!<br/>- Hide!

1161
01:52:11,848 --> 01:52:16,848
- Hurry!<br/>- Take cover!

1162
01:52:47,967 --> 01:52:50,469
Spies of Saruman.

1163
01:52:50,470 --> 01:52:54,931
The passage south is being watched.

1164
01:52:54,932 --> 01:52:59,932
We must take the Pass of Caradhras.

1165
01:53:10,907 --> 01:53:15,907
ARAGORN:<br/>Frodo!

1166
01:53:31,594 --> 01:53:34,096
Boromir.

1167
01:53:34,097 --> 01:53:38,517
It is a strange fate that we should<br/>suffer so much fear and doubt...

1168
01:53:38,518 --> 01:53:43,518
...over so small a thing.

1169
01:53:44,857 --> 01:53:47,025
Such a little thing.

1170
01:53:47,026 --> 01:53:49,111
Boromir!

1171
01:53:49,112 --> 01:53:54,112
Give the Ring to Frodo.

1172
01:54:01,624 --> 01:54:04,376
As you wish.

1173
01:54:04,377 --> 01:54:09,377
I care not.

1174
01:54:10,842 --> 01:54:15,842
[BOROMIR CHUCKLES]

1175
01:54:23,563 --> 01:54:28,563
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

1176
01:54:41,789 --> 01:54:46,710
So, Gandalf, you try<br/>to lead them over Caradhras.

1177
01:54:46,711 --> 01:54:51,711
And if that fails,<br/>where then will you go?

1178
01:54:52,592 --> 01:54:55,802
<i>If the mountain defeats you...</i>

1179
01:54:55,803 --> 01:55:00,803
<i>...will you risk<br/>a more dangerous road?</i>

1180
01:55:06,731 --> 01:55:11,731
[SARUMAN CHANTS IN QUENYA]

1181
01:55:12,570 --> 01:55:16,573
There is a fell voice on the air.

1182
01:55:16,574 --> 01:55:21,574
It's Saruman!

1183
01:55:26,959 --> 01:55:31,922
He's trying to bring down the mountain!<br/>Gandalf, we must turn back!

1184
01:55:31,923 --> 01:55:36,718
No!

1185
01:55:36,719 --> 01:55:41,719
[CHANTS IN SINDARIN]

1186
01:56:40,157 --> 01:56:42,492
We must get off the mountain!

1187
01:56:42,493 --> 01:56:46,997
Make for the Gap of Rohan,<br/>and take the west road to my city!

1188
01:56:46,998 --> 01:56:50,500
The Gap of Rohan takes us<br/>too close to lsengard!

1189
01:56:50,501 --> 01:56:54,504
GIMLI: We cannot pass over a mountain.<br/>Let us go under it.

1190
01:56:54,505 --> 01:56:59,175
Let us go through the Mines of Moria.

1191
01:56:59,176 --> 01:57:03,680
<i>SARUMAN". Moria. You fear to go<br/>into those mines.</i>

1192
01:57:03,681 --> 01:57:08,681
The Dwarves delved too greedily<br/>and too deep.

1193
01:57:09,520 --> 01:57:14,520
<i>You know what they awoke<br/>in the darkness of Khazad-dfim:</i>

1194
01:57:15,693 --> 01:57:20,693
Shadow and flame.

1195
01:57:22,533 --> 01:57:27,533
Let the Ring-bearer decide.

1196
01:57:29,916 --> 01:57:32,208
We cannot stay here!

1197
01:57:32,209 --> 01:57:35,211
This will be the death of the Hobbits.

1198
01:57:35,212 --> 01:57:39,925
Frodo?

1199
01:57:39,926 --> 01:57:43,553
We will go through the mines.

1200
01:57:43,554 --> 01:57:48,554
So be it.

1201
01:57:52,104 --> 01:57:57,104
Frodo, come and help an old man.

1202
01:57:59,570 --> 01:58:01,988
How is your shoulder?

1203
01:58:01,989 --> 01:58:06,785
- Better than it was.<br/>- And the Ring?

1204
01:58:06,786 --> 01:58:09,788
You feel its power growing, don't you?

1205
01:58:09,789 --> 01:58:13,124
I've felt it too.<br/>You must be careful now.

1206
01:58:13,125 --> 01:58:17,212
Evil will be drawn to you<br/>from outside the Fellowship.

1207
01:58:17,213 --> 01:58:22,213
And, I fear, from within.

1208
01:58:22,426 --> 01:58:26,763
- Who then do I trust?<br/>- You must trust yourself.

1209
01:58:26,764 --> 01:58:29,808
Trust your own strengths.

1210
01:58:29,809 --> 01:58:32,602
- What do you mean?<br/>- There are many powers in this world...

1211
01:58:32,603 --> 01:58:34,813
...for good or for evil.

1212
01:58:34,814 --> 01:58:37,649
Some are greater than I am.

1213
01:58:37,650 --> 01:58:42,650
And against some I have not yet<br/>been tested.

1214
01:58:42,655 --> 01:58:44,739
The walls...

1215
01:58:44,740 --> 01:58:49,740
...of Moria.

1216
01:58:52,540 --> 01:58:55,750
Dwarf doors are invisible when closed.

1217
01:58:55,751 --> 01:59:00,547
GANDALF: Their own masters cannot find<br/>them if their secrets are forgotten.

1218
01:59:00,548 --> 01:59:05,548
Why doesn't that surprise me?

1219
01:59:11,058 --> 01:59:14,561
Well, let's see.

1220
01:59:14,562 --> 01:59:16,563
Ithildin.

1221
01:59:16,564 --> 01:59:21,564
It mirrors only starlight<br/>and moonlight.

1222
01:59:33,998 --> 01:59:38,668
It reads, "The Doors of Durin,<br/>Lord of Moria.

1223
01:59:38,669 --> 01:59:43,506
- Speak, friend, and enter."<br/>- What do you suppose that means?

1224
01:59:43,507 --> 01:59:48,507
It's simple. If you are a friend, you speak<br/>the password and the doors will open.

1225
01:59:48,846 --> 01:59:53,846
[GANDALF SPEAKS IN ELVISH]

1226
02:00:12,036 --> 02:00:17,036
Nothing's happening.

1227
02:00:20,211 --> 02:00:24,756
I once knew every spell<br/>in all the tongues of Elves...

1228
02:00:24,757 --> 02:00:27,842
...Men and Orcs.

1229
02:00:27,843 --> 02:00:29,260
What are you going to do, then?

1230
02:00:29,261 --> 02:00:31,763
Knock your head against these doors,<br/>Peregrin Took!

1231
02:00:31,764 --> 02:00:33,932
And if that does not shatter them...

1232
02:00:33,933 --> 02:00:36,810
...and I am allowed a little peace<br/>from foolish questions...

1233
02:00:36,811 --> 02:00:40,730
...I will try to find the opening words.

1234
02:00:40,731 --> 02:00:45,731
[GANDALF SPEAKS IN ELVISH<br/>AND DWARVISH]

1235
02:00:53,119 --> 02:00:55,870
Mines are no place for a pony.

1236
02:00:55,871 --> 02:01:00,871
- Even one so brave as Bill.<br/>- Bye-bye, Bill.

1237
02:01:01,127 --> 02:01:04,462
Go on, Bill. Go on.

1238
02:01:04,463 --> 02:01:09,463
Don't worry, Sam,<br/>he knows the way home.

1239
02:01:14,807 --> 02:01:17,600
Do not disturb the water.

1240
02:01:17,601 --> 02:01:22,601
Oh, it's useless.

1241
02:01:32,158 --> 02:01:37,078
It's a riddle.

1242
02:01:37,079 --> 02:01:40,582
"Speak 'friend' and enter."

1243
02:01:40,583 --> 02:01:44,961
What's the Elvish word for "friend"?

1244
02:01:44,962 --> 02:01:49,962
<i>Mellon.</i>

1245
02:02:04,315 --> 02:02:09,315
GIMLI: Soon, Master Elf, you will enjoy<br/>the fabled hospitality of the Dwarves.

1246
02:02:09,653 --> 02:02:14,653
Roaring fires, malt beer,<br/>ripe meat off the bone!

1247
02:02:16,869 --> 02:02:20,330
This, my friend,<br/>is the home of my cousin Balin.

1248
02:02:20,331 --> 02:02:22,916
And they call it a mine.

1249
02:02:22,917 --> 02:02:25,919
A mine!

1250
02:02:25,920 --> 02:02:30,920
This is no mine. It's a tomb.

1251
02:02:33,510 --> 02:02:35,386
GIMLI:<br/>No.

1252
02:02:35,387 --> 02:02:38,223
No...

1253
02:02:38,224 --> 02:02:42,518
No!

1254
02:02:42,519 --> 02:02:47,519
Goblins.

1255
02:02:47,983 --> 02:02:52,983
We make for the Gap of Rohan.<br/>We should never have come here.

1256
02:02:53,364 --> 02:02:58,364
ARAGORN:<br/>Now, get out of here. Get out!

1257
02:02:58,702 --> 02:03:01,287
MERRY: Frodo!<br/>FRODO: Help!

1258
02:03:01,288 --> 02:03:03,081
Strider!

1259
02:03:03,082 --> 02:03:06,042
FRODO: Help!<br/>SAM: Get off him!

1260
02:03:06,043 --> 02:03:11,043
Aragorn!

1261
02:03:17,513 --> 02:03:19,722
Frodo!

1262
02:03:19,723 --> 02:03:24,723
Strider!

1263
02:03:44,915 --> 02:03:46,124
Into the mines!

1264
02:03:46,125 --> 02:03:51,125
- Legolas!<br/>ARAGORN: Into the cave!

1265
02:03:53,632 --> 02:03:58,632
Run!

1266
02:04:12,276 --> 02:04:16,070
GANDALF:<br/>We now have but one choice.

1267
02:04:16,071 --> 02:04:21,071
We must face the long dark of Moria.

1268
02:04:21,201 --> 02:04:23,369
Be on your guard.

1269
02:04:23,370 --> 02:04:26,998
There are older<br/>and fouler things than Orcs...

1270
02:04:26,999 --> 02:04:31,999
...in the deep places of the world.

1271
02:04:38,510 --> 02:04:42,638
Quietly now. It's a four-day journey<br/>to the other side.

1272
02:04:42,639 --> 02:04:47,639
Let us hope that our presence<br/>may go unnoticed.

1273
02:05:32,272 --> 02:05:36,150
The wealth of Moria is not in gold...

1274
02:05:36,151 --> 02:05:38,736
...or jewels...

1275
02:05:38,737 --> 02:05:43,737
...but mithril.

1276
02:06:00,134 --> 02:06:05,134
Bilbo had a shirt of mithril rings<br/>that Thorin gave him.

1277
02:06:05,264 --> 02:06:09,392
- Oh, that was a kingly gift.<br/>- Yes.

1278
02:06:09,393 --> 02:06:11,477
I never told him...

1279
02:06:11,478 --> 02:06:16,478
...but its worth was greater than<br/>the value of the Shire.

1280
02:06:28,787 --> 02:06:33,787
Pippin.

1281
02:06:51,185 --> 02:06:55,897
I have no memory of this place.

1282
02:06:55,898 --> 02:06:57,607
PIPPIN: Are we lost?<br/>MERRY: No.

1283
02:06:57,608 --> 02:07:00,276
PIPPIN: I think we are.<br/>MERRY: Gandalf's thinking.

1284
02:07:00,277 --> 02:07:02,028
PIPPIN: Merry?<br/>MERRY: What?

1285
02:07:02,029 --> 02:07:07,029
PIPPIN:<br/>I'm hungry.

1286
02:07:15,292 --> 02:07:19,962
- There's something down there.<br/>-It's Gollum.

1287
02:07:19,963 --> 02:07:24,300
- Gollum?<br/>- He's been following us for three days.

1288
02:07:24,301 --> 02:07:29,138
- He escaped the dungeons of Barad-dï¬‚r?<br/>- Escaped...

1289
02:07:29,139 --> 02:07:31,307
...or was set loose.

1290
02:07:31,308 --> 02:07:36,308
Now the Ring has brought him here.

1291
02:07:37,606 --> 02:07:40,483
He will never be rid of his need for it.

1292
02:07:40,484 --> 02:07:45,484
He hates and loves the Ring,<br/>as he hates and loves himself.

1293
02:07:46,448 --> 02:07:51,448
SmÃ©agol's life is a sad story.

1294
02:07:51,495 --> 02:07:56,495
Yes, Smeagol he was once called.<br/>Before the Ring found him.

1295
02:07:58,335 --> 02:08:01,462
Before it drove him mad.

1296
02:08:01,463 --> 02:08:04,507
It's a pity Bilbo didn't kill him<br/>when he had the chance.

1297
02:08:04,508 --> 02:08:06,801
Pity?

1298
02:08:06,802 --> 02:08:10,596
It is pity that stayed Bilbo's hand.

1299
02:08:10,597 --> 02:08:15,597
Many that live deserve death.<br/>Some that die deserve life.

1300
02:08:17,229 --> 02:08:22,149
Can you give it to them, Frodo?

1301
02:08:22,150 --> 02:08:26,320
Do not be too eager<br/>to deal out death and judgment.

1302
02:08:26,321 --> 02:08:29,824
Even the very wise<br/>cannot see all ends.

1303
02:08:29,825 --> 02:08:34,825
My heart tells me that Gollum has some<br/>part to play yet, for good or ill...

1304
02:08:36,540 --> 02:08:40,876
...before this is over.

1305
02:08:40,877 --> 02:08:45,877
The pity of Bilbo<br/>may rule the fate of many.

1306
02:08:51,388 --> 02:08:56,183
I wish the Ring<br/>had never come to me.

1307
02:08:56,184 --> 02:08:58,394
I wish none of this had happened.

1308
02:08:58,395 --> 02:09:03,395
So do all who live to see such times.<br/>But that is not for them to decide.

1309
02:09:04,234 --> 02:09:09,234
All we have to decide is what to do<br/>with the time that is given to us.

1310
02:09:11,241 --> 02:09:15,661
There are other forces at work in this<br/>world, Frodo, besides the will of evil.

1311
02:09:15,662 --> 02:09:18,581
Bilbo was meant to find the Ring.

1312
02:09:18,582 --> 02:09:23,085
In which case,<br/>you also were meant to have it.

1313
02:09:23,086 --> 02:09:28,086
And that is an encouraging thought.

1314
02:09:29,217 --> 02:09:31,177
Ah!

1315
02:09:31,178 --> 02:09:33,262
It's that way.

1316
02:09:33,263 --> 02:09:35,765
- He's remembered.<br/>GAN DALF: No.

1317
02:09:35,766 --> 02:09:39,769
But the air doesn't smell<br/>so foul down here.

1318
02:09:39,770 --> 02:09:44,770
If in doubt, Meriadoc,<br/>always follow your nose.

1319
02:09:59,790 --> 02:10:04,790
Let me risk a little more light.

1320
02:10:08,632 --> 02:10:11,133
Behold...

1321
02:10:11,134 --> 02:10:16,134
...the great realm<br/>and Dwarf-city of Dwarrowdelf.

1322
02:10:18,809 --> 02:10:23,809
There's an eye opener, and no mistake.

1323
02:10:47,170 --> 02:10:52,170
Gimli!

1324
02:10:54,678 --> 02:10:56,345
No.

1325
02:10:56,346 --> 02:11:00,516
No!

1326
02:11:00,517 --> 02:11:05,517
Oh, no.

1327
02:11:05,522 --> 02:11:10,522
No.

1328
02:11:14,072 --> 02:11:16,532
GANDALF:<br/>"Here lies Balin...

1329
02:11:16,533 --> 02:11:18,868
...son of Fundin...

1330
02:11:18,869 --> 02:11:22,538
...Lord of Moria."

1331
02:11:22,539 --> 02:11:26,375
He is dead, then.

1332
02:11:26,376 --> 02:11:31,376
It's as I feared.

1333
02:11:38,889 --> 02:11:43,889
[GIMLI SPEAKS DWARVISH]

1334
02:11:45,896 --> 02:11:49,023
We must move on. We cannot linger.

1335
02:11:49,024 --> 02:11:54,024
GANDALF: "They have taken the bridge<br/>and the second hall.

1336
02:11:54,821 --> 02:11:58,073
We have barred the gates...

1337
02:11:58,074 --> 02:12:00,743
...but cannot hold them for long.

1338
02:12:00,744 --> 02:12:03,954
The ground shakes.

1339
02:12:03,955 --> 02:12:05,915
Drums...

1340
02:12:05,916 --> 02:12:10,916
...drums in the deep.

1341
02:12:12,881 --> 02:12:16,926
We cannot get out.

1342
02:12:16,927 --> 02:12:21,927
A Shadow moves in the dark.

1343
02:12:22,432 --> 02:12:27,432
We cannot get out.

1344
02:12:27,979 --> 02:12:32,979
They are coming."

1345
02:12:33,109 --> 02:12:38,109
[CLATTERING]

1346
02:12:52,379 --> 02:12:57,379
[THUDDING]

1347
02:13:01,596 --> 02:13:06,596
[SILENCE]

1348
02:13:12,983 --> 02:13:15,150
Fool of a Took!

1349
02:13:15,151 --> 02:13:20,151
Throw yourself in next time,<br/>and rid us of your stupidity.

1350
02:13:22,617 --> 02:13:27,617
[DRUMS BEATING]

1351
02:13:35,672 --> 02:13:40,672
[SCREECHING]

1352
02:13:44,931 --> 02:13:48,851
SAM:<br/>Frodo!

1353
02:13:48,852 --> 02:13:53,852
Orcs.

1354
02:13:57,360 --> 02:14:02,360
Get back! Stay close to Gandalf!

1355
02:14:06,661 --> 02:14:11,661
They have a cave-troll.

1356
02:14:24,220 --> 02:14:25,888
Let them come!

1357
02:14:25,889 --> 02:14:30,889
There is one Dwarf yet in Moria<br/>who still draws breath.

1358
02:14:44,616 --> 02:14:49,616
[SCREECHES]

1359
02:16:48,364 --> 02:16:53,364
I think I'm getting the hang of this.

1360
02:16:55,872 --> 02:17:00,872
Frodo!

1361
02:17:31,074 --> 02:17:33,909
FRODO:<br/>Aragorn! Aragorn!

1362
02:17:33,910 --> 02:17:38,910
Frodo!

1363
02:18:20,957 --> 02:18:25,627
Frodo!

1364
02:18:25,628 --> 02:18:30,628
Frodo!

1365
02:19:23,061 --> 02:19:27,189
Oh, no.

1366
02:19:27,190 --> 02:19:32,190
[FRODO GROANS]

1367
02:19:32,779 --> 02:19:37,074
He's alive.

1368
02:19:37,075 --> 02:19:40,369
I'm all right. I'm not hurt.

1369
02:19:40,370 --> 02:19:42,788
You should be dead.

1370
02:19:42,789 --> 02:19:45,540
That spear would have skewered<br/>a wild boar.

1371
02:19:45,541 --> 02:19:50,541
I think there's more to this Hobbit<br/>than meets the eye.

1372
02:19:56,094 --> 02:20:00,013
Mithril.

1373
02:20:00,014 --> 02:20:03,058
You are full of surprises,<br/>Master Baggins.

1374
02:20:03,059 --> 02:20:08,059
[SCREECHING]

1375
02:20:08,606 --> 02:20:13,606
To the Bridge of Khazad-dfim!

1376
02:20:25,540 --> 02:20:30,540
ARAGORN:<br/>This way!

1377
02:21:10,752 --> 02:21:15,752
[GROWLING]

1378
02:21:37,528 --> 02:21:42,528
What is this new devilry?

1379
02:21:54,670 --> 02:21:56,630
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1380
02:21:56,631 --> 02:21:59,716
A Balrog.

1381
02:21:59,717 --> 02:22:04,717
A demon of the ancient world.

1382
02:22:05,056 --> 02:22:08,683
This foe is beyond any of you.

1383
02:22:08,684 --> 02:22:13,684
Run!

1384
02:22:17,568 --> 02:22:22,568
Quickly!

1385
02:22:35,711 --> 02:22:37,587
Gandalf.

1386
02:22:37,588 --> 02:22:40,590
Lead them on, Aragorn.

1387
02:22:40,591 --> 02:22:43,343
The bridge is near.

1388
02:22:43,344 --> 02:22:45,178
[BALROG GROWLS]

1389
02:22:45,179 --> 02:22:50,179
Do as I say!<br/>Swords are no more use here.

1390
02:23:18,421 --> 02:23:23,421
Gandalf!

1391
02:23:38,441 --> 02:23:43,441
BOROMIR:<br/>Merry! Pippin!

1392
02:23:50,786 --> 02:23:55,040
Sam!

1393
02:23:55,041 --> 02:24:00,041
Nobody tosses a Dwarf.

1394
02:24:01,297 --> 02:24:06,297
Not the beard!

1395
02:24:15,978 --> 02:24:19,981
Steady.

1396
02:24:19,982 --> 02:24:24,611
Hold on!

1397
02:24:24,612 --> 02:24:27,572
[BALROG GROWLS]

1398
02:24:27,573 --> 02:24:32,573
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1399
02:24:42,672 --> 02:24:47,672
Hang on!

1400
02:24:54,684 --> 02:24:59,354
Lean forward!

1401
02:24:59,355 --> 02:25:01,731
Steady.

1402
02:25:01,732 --> 02:25:03,149
Come on!

1403
02:25:03,150 --> 02:25:08,150
NOW!

1404
02:25:21,877 --> 02:25:23,878
Over the bridge!

1405
02:25:23,879 --> 02:25:28,879
Fly!

1406
02:26:10,092 --> 02:26:12,302
You cannot pass!

1407
02:26:12,303 --> 02:26:17,303
Gandalf!

1408
02:26:18,184 --> 02:26:23,184
I am a servant of the Secret Fire,<br/>wielder of the flame of Anor.

1409
02:26:24,065 --> 02:26:29,065
The dark fire will not avail you,<br/>flame of Udfm!

1410
02:26:37,828 --> 02:26:42,828
Go back to the Shadow.

1411
02:26:47,630 --> 02:26:52,630
You shall not pass!

1412
02:27:19,245 --> 02:27:24,245
BOROMIR: No! No!<br/>- Gandalf!

1413
02:27:30,798 --> 02:27:35,798
Fly, you fools!

1414
02:27:37,388 --> 02:27:42,388
No!

1415
02:27:45,688 --> 02:27:50,688
Aragorn!

1416
02:28:45,122 --> 02:28:50,122
Legolas, get them up.

1417
02:28:52,087 --> 02:28:54,088
Give them a moment, for pity's sake!

1418
02:28:54,089 --> 02:28:57,926
By nightfall, these hills will<br/>be swarming with Orcs.

1419
02:28:57,927 --> 02:29:02,138
We must reach the woods of LothlÃ©rien.

1420
02:29:02,139 --> 02:29:06,935
Come, Boromir. Legolas.<br/>Gimli, get them up.

1421
02:29:06,936 --> 02:29:09,479
On your feet, Sam.

1422
02:29:09,480 --> 02:29:13,066
Frodo?

1423
02:29:13,067 --> 02:29:18,067
Frodo!

1424
02:30:07,288 --> 02:30:10,540
Stay close, young Hobbits!

1425
02:30:10,541 --> 02:30:14,919
They say that a great sorceress<br/>lives in these woods.

1426
02:30:14,920 --> 02:30:18,006
An Elf-witch...

1427
02:30:18,007 --> 02:30:21,426
...of terrible power.

1428
02:30:21,427 --> 02:30:23,845
All who look upon her...

1429
02:30:23,846 --> 02:30:25,847
...fall under her spell.

1430
02:30:25,848 --> 02:30:29,392
FEMALE VOICE:<br/>Frodo!

1431
02:30:29,393 --> 02:30:31,644
And are never seen again.

1432
02:30:31,645 --> 02:30:36,357
FEMALE <i>VOICE: Your coming to us is<br/>as the footsteps of doom.</i>

1433
02:30:36,358 --> 02:30:40,236
<i>You bring great evil here,<br/>Ring-bearer.</i>

1434
02:30:40,237 --> 02:30:45,237
SAM:<br/>Mr. Frodo?

1435
02:30:47,328 --> 02:30:52,328
Well, here's one Dwarf<br/>she won't ensnare so easily.

1436
02:30:53,083 --> 02:30:58,083
I have the eyes of a hawk<br/>and the ears of a fox.

1437
02:31:05,346 --> 02:31:10,346
The Dwarf breathes so loud,<br/>we could have shot him in the dark.

1438
02:31:15,064 --> 02:31:17,982
[IN ELVISH]<br/>Welcome Legolas, son of Thranduil.

1439
02:31:17,983 --> 02:31:22,983
[IN ELVISH]<br/>Our Fellowship stands in your debt.

1440
02:31:23,489 --> 02:31:25,823
Aragorn of the Dunedain...

1441
02:31:25,824 --> 02:31:28,076
you are known to us.

1442
02:31:28,077 --> 02:31:30,536
So much for the legendary courtesy<br/>of the Elves!

1443
02:31:30,537 --> 02:31:32,580
Speak words we can all understand!

1444
02:31:32,581 --> 02:31:37,502
[IN ENGLISH] We have not had dealings<br/>with the Dwarves since the Dark Days.

1445
02:31:37,503 --> 02:31:40,421
And you know what this Dwarf<br/>says to that?

1446
02:31:40,422 --> 02:31:45,422
[SPEAKS IN DWARVISH]

1447
02:31:46,929 --> 02:31:51,929
That was not so courteous.

1448
02:31:55,437 --> 02:32:00,437
You bring great evil with you.

1449
02:32:01,235 --> 02:32:06,235
You can go no further.

1450
02:32:09,576 --> 02:32:14,576
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1451
02:32:40,691 --> 02:32:44,485
Gandalf's death was not in vain.

1452
02:32:44,486 --> 02:32:47,864
Nor would he have you give up hope.

1453
02:32:47,865 --> 02:32:52,076
You carry a heavy burden, Frodo.

1454
02:32:52,077 --> 02:32:57,077
Don't carry the weight of the dead.

1455
02:32:58,167 --> 02:33:03,167
You will follow me.

1456
02:33:11,889 --> 02:33:14,515
Caras Galadhon.

1457
02:33:14,516 --> 02:33:17,643
The heart of Elvendom on earth.

1458
02:33:17,644 --> 02:33:22,644
Realm of the Lord Celeborn<br/>and of Galadriel, Lady of Light.

1459
02:34:42,312 --> 02:34:46,107
The enemy knows you have entered here.

1460
02:34:46,108 --> 02:34:51,108
What hope you had in secrecy<br/>is now gone.

1461
02:34:52,990 --> 02:34:57,702
Eight there are here, yet nine there<br/>were set out from Rivendell.

1462
02:34:57,703 --> 02:34:59,704
Tell me, where is Gandalf?

1463
02:34:59,705 --> 02:35:02,957
For I much desire to speak with him.

1464
02:35:02,958 --> 02:35:06,627
I can no longer see him from afar.

1465
02:35:06,628 --> 02:35:11,628
GALADRIEL: Gandalf the Grey did not<br/>pass the borders of this land.

1466
02:35:12,092 --> 02:35:17,092
He has fallen into Shadow.

1467
02:35:19,224 --> 02:35:24,224
He was taken by both Shadow and flame.

1468
02:35:25,355 --> 02:35:29,817
A Balrog of Morgoth.

1469
02:35:29,818 --> 02:35:34,818
For we went needlessly<br/>into the net of Moria.

1470
02:35:35,324 --> 02:35:39,160
Needless were none of the deeds<br/>of Gandalf in life.

1471
02:35:39,161 --> 02:35:44,161
We do not yet know his full purpose.

1472
02:35:47,252 --> 02:35:51,839
Do not let the great emptiness<br/>of Khazad-dfim fill your heart...

1473
02:35:51,840 --> 02:35:55,176
...Gimli, son of GlÃ©in.

1474
02:35:55,177 --> 02:36:00,177
For the world has grown<br/>full of peril...

1475
02:36:00,182 --> 02:36:03,017
...and in all lands...

1476
02:36:03,018 --> 02:36:08,018
...love is now mingled with grief.

1477
02:36:19,159 --> 02:36:22,370
What now becomes of this Fellowship?

1478
02:36:22,371 --> 02:36:27,371
Without Gandalf, hope is lost.

1479
02:36:28,377 --> 02:36:31,837
The quest stands upon the edge<br/>of a knife.

1480
02:36:31,838 --> 02:36:35,675
Stray but a little and it will fail...

1481
02:36:35,676 --> 02:36:40,676
...to the ruin of all.

1482
02:36:42,849 --> 02:36:47,849
Yet hope remains<br/>while the Company is true.

1483
02:36:50,232 --> 02:36:55,232
Do not let your hearts be troubled.<br/>Go now and rest...

1484
02:36:55,404 --> 02:37:00,404
...for you are weary with sorrow<br/>and much toil.

1485
02:37:01,326 --> 02:37:03,577
Tonight, you will sleep...

1486
02:37:03,578 --> 02:37:08,578
GALADRIEL:<br/><i>Welcome, Frodo of the Shire...</i>

1487
02:37:08,583 --> 02:37:12,920
<i>...one who has seen the Eye!</i>

1488
02:37:12,921 --> 02:37:17,921
[SINGING IN ELVISH]

1489
02:37:25,058 --> 02:37:30,058
A lament for Gandalf.

1490
02:37:34,901 --> 02:37:36,652
What do they say about him?

1491
02:37:36,653 --> 02:37:41,653
I have not the heart to tell you.

1492
02:37:42,075 --> 02:37:47,075
For me, the grief is still too near.

1493
02:37:47,289 --> 02:37:50,291
I bet they don't mention his fireworks.

1494
02:37:50,292 --> 02:37:55,292
There should be a verse about them.

1495
02:37:56,882 --> 02:37:59,967
<i>The finest rockets ever seen</i>

1496
02:37:59,968 --> 02:38:03,763
<i>They burst in stars of blue and green</i>

1497
02:38:03,764 --> 02:38:07,433
<i>Or after thunder, silver showers</i>

1498
02:38:07,434 --> 02:38:09,643
[GIMLI SNORES]

1499
02:38:09,644 --> 02:38:12,646
<i>Came falling like a rain of flowers</i>

1500
02:38:12,647 --> 02:38:17,647
Oh, that doesn't do them justice<br/>by a long road.

1501
02:38:27,329 --> 02:38:30,206
ARAGORN:<br/>Take some rest.

1502
02:38:30,207 --> 02:38:33,125
These borders are well-protected.

1503
02:38:33,126 --> 02:38:38,126
I will find no rest here.

1504
02:38:38,507 --> 02:38:41,717
I heard her voice inside my head.

1505
02:38:41,718 --> 02:38:45,679
She spoke of my father<br/>and the fall of Gondor.

1506
02:38:45,680 --> 02:38:50,680
She said to me,<br/>"Even now there is hope left."

1507
02:38:52,521 --> 02:38:56,690
But I cannot see it.

1508
02:38:56,691 --> 02:39:01,691
It is long since we had any hope.

1509
02:39:09,371 --> 02:39:12,248
My father is a noble man.

1510
02:39:12,249 --> 02:39:14,834
But his rule is failing...

1511
02:39:14,835 --> 02:39:19,835
...and our people lose faith.

1512
02:39:21,675 --> 02:39:25,386
He looks to me to make things right,<br/>and I would do it.

1513
02:39:25,387 --> 02:39:30,387
I would see the glory<br/>of Gondor restored.

1514
02:39:31,726 --> 02:39:35,396
Have you ever seen it, Aragorn?

1515
02:39:35,397 --> 02:39:37,565
The White Tower of Ecthelion.

1516
02:39:37,566 --> 02:39:42,069
Glimmering like a spike<br/>of pearl and silver.

1517
02:39:42,070 --> 02:39:47,070
Its banners caught high<br/>in the morning breeze.

1518
02:39:48,493 --> 02:39:50,619
Have you ever been called home...

1519
02:39:50,620 --> 02:39:55,207
...by the clear ringing<br/>of silver trumpets?

1520
02:39:55,208 --> 02:39:58,752
I have seen the White City...

1521
02:39:58,753 --> 02:40:01,255
...long ago.

1522
02:40:01,256 --> 02:40:06,256
One day, our paths will lead us there.

1523
02:40:07,137 --> 02:40:10,556
And the tower guard<br/>shall take up the call:

1524
02:40:10,557 --> 02:40:15,557
"The Lords of Gondor have returned."

1525
02:41:21,086 --> 02:41:23,796
Will you look into the mirror?

1526
02:41:23,797 --> 02:41:28,300
What will I see?

1527
02:41:28,301 --> 02:41:31,512
Even the wisest cannot tell.

1528
02:41:31,513 --> 02:41:33,597
For the mirror...

1529
02:41:33,598 --> 02:41:38,598
...shows many things.

1530
02:41:39,145 --> 02:41:41,730
Things that were...

1531
02:41:41,731 --> 02:41:45,109
...things that are...

1532
02:41:45,110 --> 02:41:50,110
...and some things...

1533
02:41:50,615 --> 02:41:55,615
...that have not yet come to pass.

1534
02:42:57,807 --> 02:43:02,807
[VOICES SPEAKING IN BLACK SPEECH]

1535
02:43:16,451 --> 02:43:21,451
I know what it is you saw.

1536
02:43:21,748 --> 02:43:26,001
For it is also in my mind.

1537
02:43:26,002 --> 02:43:31,002
<i>It is what will come to pass<br/>if you should fail.</i>

1538
02:43:32,467 --> 02:43:37,467
<i>The Fellowship is breaking.<br/>It is already begun.</i>

1539
02:43:37,972 --> 02:43:41,475
<i>He will try to take the Ring.</i>

1540
02:43:41,476 --> 02:43:44,478
<i>You know of whom I speak.</i>

1541
02:43:44,479 --> 02:43:49,479
<i>One by one, it will destroy them all.</i>

1542
02:43:50,652 --> 02:43:53,487
<i>FRODO:<br/>If you ask it of</i> me...

1543
02:43:53,488 --> 02:43:57,616
<i>...I will give you the One Ring.</i>

1544
02:43:57,617 --> 02:44:02,617
You offer it to me freely.

1545
02:44:04,332 --> 02:44:09,332
I do not deny that my heart<br/>has greatly desired this.

1546
02:44:14,676 --> 02:44:18,387
In place of a Dark Lord,<br/>you would have a queen...

1547
02:44:18,388 --> 02:44:22,850
...not dark but beautiful,<br/>and terrible as the dawn!

1548
02:44:22,851 --> 02:44:26,353
Treacherous as the sea!

1549
02:44:26,354 --> 02:44:31,354
Stronger than the foundations<br/>of the earth!

1550
02:44:31,776 --> 02:44:34,361
All shall love me...

1551
02:44:34,362 --> 02:44:39,362
...and despair.

1552
02:44:51,296 --> 02:44:55,883
I pass the test. I will diminish...

1553
02:44:55,884 --> 02:44:58,552
...and go into the West...

1554
02:44:58,553 --> 02:45:03,553
-...and remain Galadriel.<br/>- I cannot do this alone.

1555
02:45:06,603 --> 02:45:11,603
You are a Ring-bearer, Frodo.<br/>To bear a Ring of Power...

1556
02:45:11,691 --> 02:45:16,528
...is to be alone.

1557
02:45:16,529 --> 02:45:19,448
This is Nenya,<br/>the Ring of Adamant.

1558
02:45:19,449 --> 02:45:24,244
And I am its keeper.

1559
02:45:24,245 --> 02:45:28,916
This task was appointed to you.

1560
02:45:28,917 --> 02:45:33,045
And if you do not find a way...

1561
02:45:33,046 --> 02:45:35,422
...no one will.

1562
02:45:35,423 --> 02:45:39,259
Then I know what I must do.

1563
02:45:39,260 --> 02:45:43,722
It's just...

1564
02:45:43,723 --> 02:45:48,723
...I'm afraid to do it.

1565
02:45:49,437 --> 02:45:54,437
Even the smallest person can change<br/>the course of the future.

1566
02:45:59,948 --> 02:46:04,948
Do you know how the Orcs<br/>first came into being?

1567
02:46:06,454 --> 02:46:10,958
They were Elves once.

1568
02:46:10,959 --> 02:46:14,461
Taken by the Dark Powers...

1569
02:46:14,462 --> 02:46:17,965
...tortured and mutilated.

1570
02:46:17,966 --> 02:46:22,966
A ruined and terrible form of life.

1571
02:46:23,596 --> 02:46:26,890
And now...

1572
02:46:26,891 --> 02:46:29,476
...perfected.

1573
02:46:29,477 --> 02:46:34,477
My fighting Uruk-hai...

1574
02:46:34,607 --> 02:46:37,150
...whom do you serve?

1575
02:46:37,151 --> 02:46:42,151
Saruman!

1576
02:47:00,508 --> 02:47:04,177
Hunt them down. Do not stop<br/>until they are found.

1577
02:47:04,178 --> 02:47:07,306
You do not know pain.<br/>You do not know fear.

1578
02:47:07,307 --> 02:47:12,307
You will taste Man-flesh!

1579
02:47:15,315 --> 02:47:19,192
One of the half lings carries<br/>something of great value.

1580
02:47:19,193 --> 02:47:24,193
Bring them to me alive and unspoiled.

1581
02:47:25,199 --> 02:47:30,199
Kill the others.

1582
02:47:45,678 --> 02:47:50,678
CELEBORN: Never before have we clad<br/>strangers in the garb of our own people.

1583
02:47:52,226 --> 02:47:57,226
May these cloaks help shield you<br/>from unfriendly eyes.

1584
02:48:03,237 --> 02:48:05,030
Lembas.

1585
02:48:05,031 --> 02:48:09,117
Elvish waybread.

1586
02:48:09,118 --> 02:48:14,118
One small bite is enough to fill<br/>the stomach of a grown man.

1587
02:48:18,586 --> 02:48:20,754
How many did you eat?

1588
02:48:20,755 --> 02:48:23,924
<i>Four.</i>

1589
02:48:23,925 --> 02:48:28,220
[BELCHES]

1590
02:48:28,221 --> 02:48:31,014
CELEBORN: <i>Every league you travel south,<br/>the danger will increase.</i>

1591
02:48:31,015 --> 02:48:35,268
<i>Mordor Orcs now hold the eastern shore<br/>of the Anduin.</i>

1592
02:48:35,269 --> 02:48:38,021
<i>Nor will you find safety<br/>on the western bank.</i>

1593
02:48:38,022 --> 02:48:42,025
Strange creatures bearing the White Hand<br/>have been seen on our borders.

1594
02:48:42,026 --> 02:48:47,026
Seldom do Orcs journey in the open<br/>under the sun, yet these have done so.

1595
02:48:55,790 --> 02:48:59,793
[IN ELVISH]<br/>You are being tracked.

1596
02:48:59,794 --> 02:49:01,211
[IN ENGLISH]<br/>By river you have the chance...

1597
02:49:01,212 --> 02:49:06,212
...of outrunning the enemy<br/>to the Falls of Rauros.

1598
02:49:21,691 --> 02:49:26,691
GALADRIEL: My gift for you, Legolas,<br/>is a bow of the Galadhrim.

1599
02:49:26,779 --> 02:49:31,779
Worthy of the skill<br/>of our woodland kin.

1600
02:49:35,663 --> 02:49:38,290
These are the daggers of the Noldorin.

1601
02:49:38,291 --> 02:49:41,668
They have already seen service in war.

1602
02:49:41,669 --> 02:49:44,880
Do not fear, young Peregrin Took.

1603
02:49:44,881 --> 02:49:49,881
<i>You will find your courage.</i>

1604
02:49:50,094 --> 02:49:52,220
<i>And for you, Samwise Gamgee...</i>

1605
02:49:52,221 --> 02:49:54,973
...Elven rope made of hithlain.

1606
02:49:54,974 --> 02:49:58,894
Thank you, my lady.

1607
02:49:58,895 --> 02:50:03,895
Have you run out<br/>of those nice, shiny daggers?

1608
02:50:08,696 --> 02:50:11,865
And what gift would a dwarf ask<br/>of the Elves?

1609
02:50:11,866 --> 02:50:14,659
Nothing.

1610
02:50:14,660 --> 02:50:18,622
Except to look upon the lady<br/>of the Galadhrim one last time...

1611
02:50:18,623 --> 02:50:23,623
...for she is more fair<br/>than all the jewels beneath the earth.

1612
02:50:30,885 --> 02:50:32,636
Actually...

1613
02:50:32,637 --> 02:50:35,055
There was one thing.

1614
02:50:35,056 --> 02:50:37,891
No, no, I'm talking nonsense.<br/>It's quite impossible.

1615
02:50:37,892 --> 02:50:42,892
<i>Stupid to ask.</i>

1616
02:50:43,231 --> 02:50:45,565
GALADRIEL:<br/><i>I have nothing greater to give...</i>

1617
02:50:45,566 --> 02:50:50,362
...than the gift you already bear.

1618
02:50:50,363 --> 02:50:52,697
[IN ELVISH]<br/>For her love,

1619
02:50:52,698 --> 02:50:57,698
I fear the grace of Arwen Evenstar<br/>will diminish.

1620
02:50:58,788 --> 02:51:03,667
[IN ELVISH]<br/>I would have her leave these shores,

1621
02:51:03,668 --> 02:51:08,588
and be with her people.

1622
02:51:08,589 --> 02:51:13,589
I would have her take the ship to Valinor.

1623
02:51:14,804 --> 02:51:18,473
[IN ENGLISH]<br/>That choice is yet before her.

1624
02:51:18,474 --> 02:51:21,726
You have your own choice to make,<br/>Aragorn.

1625
02:51:21,727 --> 02:51:26,727
To rise above the height of all<br/>your fathers since the days of Elendil...

1626
02:51:27,733 --> 02:51:32,733
...or to fall into darkness<br/>with all that is left of your kin.

1627
02:51:39,203 --> 02:51:44,203
[IN ELVISH]<br/>Farewell.

1628
02:51:44,375 --> 02:51:49,375
There is much you have yet to do.

1629
02:51:54,260 --> 02:51:55,719
We shall not meet again...

1630
02:51:55,720 --> 02:51:59,639
Elessar.

1631
02:51:59,640 --> 02:52:02,976
<i>[IN ENGLISH]<br/>Farewell, Frodo Baggins.</i>

1632
02:52:02,977 --> 02:52:07,147
I give you the light of EÃ©rendil...

1633
02:52:07,148 --> 02:52:12,148
...our most beloved star.

1634
02:52:18,659 --> 02:52:23,288
<i>May it be a light for you<br/>in dark places...</i>

1635
02:52:23,289 --> 02:52:28,289
<i>...when all other lights go out.</i>

1636
02:52:36,177 --> 02:52:40,013
GIMLI: I have taken my worst wound<br/>at this parting...

1637
02:52:40,014 --> 02:52:45,014
...having looked my last upon that<br/>which is fairest.

1638
02:52:45,019 --> 02:52:48,647
Henceforth I will call nothing fair<br/>unless it be her gift to me.

1639
02:52:48,648 --> 02:52:50,774
What was her gift?

1640
02:52:50,775 --> 02:52:55,775
I asked her for one hair<br/>from her golden head.

1641
02:52:56,489 --> 02:53:01,489
She gave me three.

1642
02:54:04,890 --> 02:54:09,890
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

1643
02:54:41,510 --> 02:54:46,510
Gollum. He has tracked us since Moria.

1644
02:54:48,684 --> 02:54:52,020
I had hoped we would lose him<br/>on the river.

1645
02:54:52,021 --> 02:54:56,024
But he's too clever a Waterman.

1646
02:54:56,025 --> 02:54:59,486
And if he alerts the enemy<br/>to our whereabouts...

1647
02:54:59,487 --> 02:55:01,946
...it will make the crossing<br/>even more dangerous.

1648
02:55:01,947 --> 02:55:04,157
SAM:<br/>Have some food, Mr. Frodo.

1649
02:55:04,158 --> 02:55:07,452
- No, Sam.<br/>- You haven't eaten anything all day.

1650
02:55:07,453 --> 02:55:11,498
You're not sleeping, neither.<br/>Don't think I haven't noticed.

1651
02:55:11,499 --> 02:55:14,667
- Mr. Frodo--<br/>- I'm all right.

1652
02:55:14,668 --> 02:55:16,127
But you're not.

1653
02:55:16,128 --> 02:55:18,797
I'm hereto help you.

1654
02:55:18,798 --> 02:55:23,798
I promised Gandalf that I would.

1655
02:55:26,472 --> 02:55:31,351
You can't help me, Sam.

1656
02:55:31,352 --> 02:55:35,980
Not this time.

1657
02:55:35,981 --> 02:55:40,981
Get some sleep.

1658
02:55:44,407 --> 02:55:47,033
Minas Tirith is the safer road.

1659
02:55:47,034 --> 02:55:50,495
You know that.<br/>From there we can regroup.

1660
02:55:50,496 --> 02:55:53,039
Strike out for Mordor from a place<br/>of strength.

1661
02:55:53,040 --> 02:55:56,376
There is no strength in Gondor<br/>that can avail us.

1662
02:55:56,377 --> 02:56:00,255
You were quick enough to trust<br/>the Elves.

1663
02:56:00,256 --> 02:56:03,258
Have you so little faith<br/>in your own people?

1664
02:56:03,259 --> 02:56:06,469
Yes, there is weakness.<br/>There is frailty.

1665
02:56:06,470 --> 02:56:10,014
But there is courage also,<br/>and honor to be found in Men.

1666
02:56:10,015 --> 02:56:12,559
But you will not see that.

1667
02:56:12,560 --> 02:56:14,227
You are afraid!

1668
02:56:14,228 --> 02:56:17,063
All your life, you have hidden<br/>in the shadows.

1669
02:56:17,064 --> 02:56:22,064
Scared of who you are,<br/>of what you are.

1670
02:56:22,903 --> 02:56:27,903
I will not lead the Ring within<br/>a hundred leagues of your city.

1671
02:56:39,128 --> 02:56:42,380
Frodo.

1672
02:56:42,381 --> 02:56:47,302
The Argonath.

1673
02:56:47,303 --> 02:56:51,764
Long have I desired<br/>to look upon the kings of old.

1674
02:56:51,765 --> 02:56:56,765
My kin.

1675
02:58:12,680 --> 02:58:15,139
We cross the lake at nightfall.

1676
02:58:15,140 --> 02:58:17,892
Hide the boats and continue on foot.

1677
02:58:17,893 --> 02:58:21,813
- We approach Mordor from the North.<br/>- Oh, yes?

1678
02:58:21,814 --> 02:58:25,817
Just a simple matter of finding<br/>our way through Emyn Muil...

